title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, cinnamon and salt.
Pour the melted butter over crumbs and mix.
Let stand a few minutes.
Line bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save some crumbs for top.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Place one-half of cream cheese mixture in bottom of bowl. Slice angel food cake and lay slices on top of mixture.
Spoon pie filling on top.
Keep alternating layers until all used.
Finish with Cool Whip.
Best if sits in refrigerator overnight.

title: betty parish's hrutka (easter cheese)
directions: Place eggs, sugar and salt into a mixing bowl.
Place milk in a teflon coated saucepan.
Heat milk on medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Use your mixer to beat up egg mixture until slightly foamy.
Add egg mixture to boiling milk.
Stir rapidly with a wooden or plastic spoon.
Keep stirring frequently until mixture becomes curdy and the liquid is clear/watery.
Place large piece of cheesecloth over a colander.
Pour cured mixture into the center of the cheesecloth.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix together.
Eat on plate or in sandwich if desired.

title: rye boat
directions: Cut bread into boat shape.
Lift out center carefully and cut into strips for dipping.
Mix remaining ingredients together in small bowl.
Place filling in bread boat and garnish with parsley. Additional rye bread may be needed.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Tie cloves, allspice and cinnamon in a cheesecloth bag.
Place in 5-quart electric Dutch oven or large percolator with cider and sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Set control to warm to keep cider hot. Before serving, remove spice bag and float lemon slices.

title: katie's canned apples(just like apple pie filling - use for pies or apple crisp)
directions: Put apples in jars.
Cook the rest of ingredients (except lemon juice) and bring to a boil.
Boil until thick and transparent.
Add lemon juice.
Pour over apples in jars and cold pack for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in lightly greased 13x9x2 baking dish.
Mix chicken soup, broth, and tarragon.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle vegetables over top.
Mix flour and baking powder in bowl; add buttermilk and melted butter.
Stir to form a thin dough; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake uncovered about 1 hour until crust is lightly browned.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Combine butter and milk.
Pour over bread crumbs. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° until firm and lightly browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon surprise
directions: Mix together melted butter, nuts and flour.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Set aside and cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding and milk together.
Beat until thick.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Press in cake pan and refrigerate.

title: bark
directions: Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Cover the bottom with one layer of saltine crackers (whole).
Boil margarine and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over saltines.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour on chocolate chips and spread. Sprinkle with nuts.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: homemade sloppy joes ala ed
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and peppers.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes and crush them, using all juice.
Add tomato paste and one 6 ounce can of water Mix well and add spices to taste.
Cook to desired consistency, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Can add mushrooms, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese, etc.
Serve on warm kaiser buns.

title: chocolate covered worms
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Remove from heat; add noodles and nuts.
Mix until noodles are covered.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoons.
Let cool.
Pick up and eat.
They are delicious!

title: onion soup
directions: Brown sliced onion in the butter until dark brown (caramel colored).
Add fresh pepper to taste.
Add beef bouillon.
Simmer 1/2 hour, add dash of sherry if you would like.
Toast bread slices dark - put one on each serving, add cheese and broil until cheese browns.

title: gooey breakfast rolls
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan good with Pam.
Cover bottom of pan with chopped pecans.
Place 1 package frozen dinner rolls, cut in half, 5 or 6 across (leave room to rise).
Sprinkle pudding over rolls. Mix butter and brown sugar; pour over top.
Leave overnight to rise.
Bake 400° 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn out upside down on serving plate (cookie sheet) immediately.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: linguini with shrimp and broccoli
directions: Prepare linguini.
Meanwhile, bring chicken broth to boil, add broccoli, reduce heat and cook, covered, for 3 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In 10-inch skillet, heat oil, add shrimp and cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in broccoli, tomato, olives and red pepper.
Cook 1 to 3 minutes. Drain linguini and arrange on serving plate.
Spoon shrimp mixture over.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until nice and sticky.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: turkey-broccoli casserole
directions: Cut turkey into 1-inch pieces.
Combine with broccoli and water.
Cover; microwave on High 9 to 11 minutes.
Combine other ingredients; add to turkey.
Microwave for 7 to 8 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.
(I use cooked turkey or chicken and use cooked fresh broccoli, then just combine everything and microwave for 10 minutes.)

title: pea salad
directions: Put peas and string beans in large strainer; add cut up onion and celery.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil and salt together.
Stir until sugar and salt are melted.
Add to pea mixture and refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.

title: lite creamy spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine yogurt, mayo, dill weed and celery salt; blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp vegie dippers or a country bread, cut into pieces.
Makes 4 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together; pour dressing over mixture and mix again. Serves 10.

title: potato latkes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion into large bowl.
Stir in egg, flour, salt and pepper.
In large heavy skillet, heat 1/4 inch oil.
Drop potato mixture, a heaping tablespoonful at a time, into hot oil and flatten with a spatula.
Fry latkes several at a time about 2 minutes on one side; turn and fry on other side 1 minute or until golden.
Drain on paper towel.
Keep warm in 200° oven until all latkes are fried.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice steak thinly across grain and cut into strips 2 inches long.
Place garlic in hot oil and remove after a few minutes. Brown meat in oil.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and ginger.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until just tender.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add Ragu and water to beef; mix well. Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 1 1/2 cups of sauce mix.
Arrange a layer of noodles on top of sauce.
Spread 1/2 of the cottage cheese, then 1/2 of the Mozzarella over noodles. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Add another layer of sauce, then noodles.
Add remaining cottage cheese and Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Top with another layer of noodles, then remaining sauce, spreading to cover all edges of noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Mix with enough evaporated milk to make a thick mixture.
Pour into shallow loaf pan lined with pastry.
Spread pastry over top filling.
Let cool slow until pastry is done.

title: turkey cheese ball
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Chill several hours, then shape into ball.
Roll in parsley.
Yield: 2 1/2 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix altogether onions, saltines, beef, egg and seasonings; mix well.
Form mixture into 1-inch diameter balls.
Roll in flour (shake off excess flour by rolling in hands).
Saute in remaining butter until lightly browned.
Remove to larger pan as meatballs are browned.
When all are browned add stock.
Cover and simmer gently for 10 minutes.
As meatballs simmer the gravy will thicken. Just add a little water to thin to a smooth consistency.
Recipe can be cut down to half on all ingredients to make a smaller batch.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, blend pudding, sour cream and milk.
Heat chips and oil until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Add to pudding, beating on high speed until smooth.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate several hours.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: family favorite chicken and stuffing
directions: Put chicken pieces in bottom of a 2 or 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over chicken. Set aside.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions but adding carrots, onion and celery with seasoning packet.
Pour stuffing over chicken mixture.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer, until chicken is fork-tender.
May not take that long.
(Chicken breasts can be sliced or cut into small chunks before cooking.)

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Shred.
Save broth.
Break cornbread and slices of bread.
Mix together all other ingredients except margarine.
Add chicken.
Pour into crock-pot and add margarine on top.
Mixture is best if good and soupy.
May add some more broth from boiled chicken.
Cover.
Cook on low 4 hours or high 2 hours. Makes 16 servings.

title: crabmeat pasta salad
directions: Mix dressing and cheese well.
Add other ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Garnish with boiled eggs and serve with freshly ground black pepper if desired.

title: stuffed pepperoncini
directions: Drain peppers, slit open and remove seeds.
Combine cream cheese, bacon and onion.
Stuff peppers.

title: spinach picante pesto sauce
directions: Combine spinach, 1/4 cup picante sauce, cheese, nuts, oil and garlic in food processor or blender.
Mix until smooth.
Transfer to a small bowl. Stir in remaining picante sauce.
Toss spinach mixture with hot cooked pasta. Sprinkle with additional chopped nuts, if desired, and serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine beef stew meat, sliced carrots, potato pieces, celery, green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper on top.
Pour V-8 juice over all.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 5 hours.
Do not mix or lift lid until done.

title: lemon snowflakes
directions: In mixing bowl, combine the cake mix, topping and egg.
Beat with mixer on medium until blended.
Batter will be sticky.
Drop by teaspoonful into confectioners sugar.
Roll lightly to coat. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool completely.
Cut into cubes.
In a large bowl, layer cake cubes, pudding, candy bars and Cool Whip.
Then start over again until everything is used up.
This makes a great dessert for large gatherings.
Great when there are a lot of kids.

title: chocolate crunch cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in chocolate bits and cereal.
Add vanilla.
Press mix into rounded tablespoon and drop on lightly greased baking sheet. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool slightly. Remove.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: 7-up cake and icing
directions: Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

foamy.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into bite size pieces.
Put in heavy skillet with oil.
Brown meat.
Add soup mix and water.
Cover.
Cook over low heat several hours until meat is tender.
Check for enough water periodically.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix
all

in

at

Top the cake with chocolate buttercream frosting while it is still hot.

title: moroccan-style fish
directions: Cut fish into serving size pieces.
For sauce, in a small saucepan, combine chicken broth, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, cornstarch and five-spice powder.
Stir in dried fruit bits or raisins and celery.
Cook and stir sauce until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Cover the sauce to keep warm.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine boiling water, couscous, parsley and salt.
Cover; let stand for 5 minutes.

title: creamed chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Layer the ingredients in a greased casserole pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Bring to boil sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Stir in crackers.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with allspice.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: toad in the hole
directions: In a preheated oven at 350°, cook sausages until partially cooked.

Using a long casserole dish that the sausages have been cooked in (size of pan depends on how many are being served), pour Yorkshire Pudding batter over sausages (see recipe in this book). Remember, the more you serve, the more batter you will need.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Keep watch; you do not want it to burn.
Normally served with potatoes, vegetables and gravy.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Brown meat on both sides in oil.
Sprinkle roast with salt. Combine wine vinegar, catsup, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, Italian seasonings, dry mustard and 1/4 cup water; pour mixture over meat.
Cover meat; simmer until meat is tender, 1 3/4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt the caramels with margarine and water in saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until sauce is smooth.
Add noodles and peanuts (noodles can be broken and nuts chopped, if desired).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet greased with margarine.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and drain cucumbers. Slice; add onions and garlic. Add salt and mix; cover with ice cubes. Let stand 3 hours. Drain; remove garlic cloves. Combine sugar, spices and vinegar; heat just to boiling. Add drained cucumbers and onion slices and heat 5 minutes. Pack hot pickles loosely into clean hot jars. Seal and process in a boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla, then add flour, salt and soda.
Add chips and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt bugg's black joe cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Check often.

title: cheese and onion pie
directions: Mix cheese and flour by tossing; set aside.
Melt margarine in a large skillet and saute onion slices until tender, breaking them into rings as you stir.
Next, line the pie shell with most of the onions, then all the floured cheese and finally, top with remaining onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the top.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce to 325° for another 25 to 30 minutes or until filling sets.

title: raspberry applesauce salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and mix; add raspberries and applesauce.
Put in container to set.
Serve as salad or with Cool Whip as dessert.
(Recipe can be doubled to serve 10 to 12.)

title: mock apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cream of tartar in saucepan; bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low.
Then add 5 or 6 crackers at a time
in
syrup
until
soggy, then place in unbaked pie shell. Continue
until all crackers are used.
Pour remaining syrup over
crackers
in	pie
shell.
Dot
with	margarine. Sprinkle with
nutmeg
and
cinnamon
to taste.
Bake at 350° until edges of pie shell are brown.

title: simple reese's bars
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, powdered sugar and graham crackers. Pat mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until chilled. Melt chips and spread on crust when cooled.

title: washing compound
directions: Molasses filled and one of milk,

title: zucchini crab fakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fry in oil until golden on both sides.

title: no fry french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line jelly roll pan with foil and spray generously with cooking spray.
Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch strips. Toss in pan with oil, garlic, salt and pepper to coat well.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, tossing once or twice until potatoes are crisp and golden.
Serve immediately.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix softened cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Spread 1 can crescent rolls on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Add cream cheese on first layer of rolls with second can of rolls on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook in oven according to directions on can.
Cut into small squares.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the flour with baking soda.
Combine butter or margarine, sugars and pudding mix in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in oats and raisins.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded measuring teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: creamed mushrooms
directions: Wash and clean mushrooms; cut into slices.
Melt butter and cook mushrooms in butter for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and stir well.
Add salt and pepper.
Add cream and cook another 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serves 4 people.

title: peppi pesto pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Separate each biscuit into 3 thin layers. Place layers 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Dice Hormel pepperoni into bits, crosswise.
Press scant teaspoon (1 slice) of bits into each biscuit.
Spread with 1/2 teaspoon pesto sauce.
Top with 1/2 tablespoon cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: easy chicken salad finger sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Spread on your favorite bread.
Cut in quarters with or without crust.

title: white lasagna
directions: In a large pan, cook noodles according to package directions. Drain and set aside.
In a skillet, cook ground beef, celery, onion and garlic until meat is browned and vegetables are tender. Drain off fat.
Stir in basil, oregano, salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and Italian herb seasoning.
Add cream and cream cheese.
Cook and stir over low heat to melt cheese. Stir in wine.
Gradually add Cheddar and Gouda cheese, stirring and heating until cheese is nearly melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir together cottage cheese and egg.
Layer 1/2 of the noodles in a greased 13 x 9-inch dish. Top with 1/2 the meat sauce, 1/2 cottage cheese mix and 1/2 Mozzarella.
Repeat.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix together and bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° for 30 minutes or makes 10 tarts.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and serve over favorite salad ingredients.

title: homesteader's casserole
directions: Combine green beans in 2-quart dish.
Layer half the potatoes, sausage and cheese.
Top with remaining potatoes.
Combine vegetables, remaining sausage and cheese.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and cook in pressure cooker for 20 minutes.
Remove bones from chicken and cut into smaller pieces. Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup and spread over chicken.
Pour cup of chicken broth over other ingredients.
Cook at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable platter
directions: Arrange broccoli and cauliflower around outer edge of a 12-inch round pizza plate.
Place zucchini in center of plate; sprinkle with water.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape. Microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes, or until crisp-tender, rotating plate once.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes.
Combine butter and garlic salt in a 1-cup glass measure.
Microwave at High 55 seconds; mix well.
Lift plastic wrap from one side of plate; drain.
Remove plastic wrap.
Arrange tomato wedges around edge of plate.
Drizzle butter mixture over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese; microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; add meat, eggs, onion and seasoning. Mix well; put into pan, greased. Cover with sauce. Bake in moderate oven (350°) 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: quick pasta salad
directions: Bring vegetables to boil and turn off heat.
Let vegetables set in pan until cool and drain well.
For the best salad, vegetables should be tender, but not completely done.
Combine cooled pasta and vegetables with dressing (a little or a lot depending on your preference).
Marinate overnight.
Before serving, add thinly sliced fresh mushrooms.

title: coffee punch
directions: While coffee mixture is still warm, combine with sugar. Combine chilled coffee mixture with ice cream, chocolate milk and vanilla.
Stir together.
Decorate with Cool Whip and shaved chocolate.

title: savory chopped spinach
directions: Thaw spinach.
Blend soft cream cheese with sour cream. Combine cheese with spinach and remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter or margarine in small saucepan. Add baking chocolate and cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth. Pour into small mixing bowl. Add powdered sugar, salt, milk and vanilla; beat until well blended. Chill 10 to 15 minutes or until of spreading consistency. Makes about 2 cups frosting.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with spices, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Add nuts and olives; mix well with hands.
Add grated cheese slowly and mix.
Roll in paprika.
Makes 2 large balls. Can be frozen.

title: killer of a chocolate cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Spread pecans and coconut in bottom.
Mix cake according to directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt cream cheese and margarine in microwave. Add sugar to the cheese and margarine; mix well and pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: parker house dinner rolls
directions: Heat; do not boil, sugar, Crisco, salt and milk.
Cool to room temperature.
Add yeast and eggs.
Add flour and mix to about a biscuit consistency.
Let rise 1 hour and punch down.
Let rise an additional hour.
Roll out and cut rolls.
Melt butter in baking pan.
Dip cut rolls in butter, coating both sides.
Let rise another 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until brown about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook and peel potatoes. Slice potatoes crosswise and arrange in buttered casserole dish. Combine remaining ingredients and boil about 5 minutes. Pour over potatoes. Bake in 375° oven about 30 minutes. Baste potato slices several times. Serves 6.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa; add alternately with buttermilk and 2 ounces red food color.
Mix well.
Fold in vinegar and soda mixture.
Do not beat.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rosemary's pear salad
directions: Drain and mash pears (save juice).
Heat juice of pears and dissolve with the 2 large jellos.
Cream the cream cheese with a little milk or cream and dissolve in hot mixture.
Add crushed pears and chopped pecans.
Fold in whipped cream and let set.

title: spinach supreme bake
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and 4 eggs together.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread over batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until center is set. Cool slightly before cutting.

title: apple crisp
directions: Use 6 x 10-inch greased pan.
Put 5 to 6 cups sliced apples in pan.
Mix together rest of ingredients with fork until crumbly. Pour over apples.
Melt 1/3 cup butter and pour over mixture. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and margarine with mixer.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix and roll in 1-inch balls.
Place in freezer.

title: california chicken(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Dredge chicken in mixture.
Brown chicken in margarine in skillet.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for one hour.
Baste every 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings at 322 calories each.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add dried fruit, if you wish.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles 15 minutes; drain.
Brown meat, add spaghetti sauce.
Blend cottage cheese with eggs.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread layer of sauce, top with noodles, cottage cheese and egg mixture, noodles, top with sauce, Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and cut.

title: pineapple fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add juice and fruit last. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Wrap in cheesecloth and moisten with orange juice.

title: apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, use juice.
Cook first 4 ingredients until thick; chill, then fold in pineapple, apples, marshmallows, diced apples and peanuts.
Cool.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour over steak in crock-pot for 4 to 7 hours. Pour over noodles or rice.

title: miracle cabbage soup
directions: Cut
vegetables and cover with water in large pot.
Add onion soup mix, garlic, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: tortellini and spinach salad
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil.
Stir in tortellini and follow directions on package.
Stir in peas and boil per directions.
Drain and cool under cold running water.
Drain well and place in serving bowl.
Sprinkle with olive oil, toss, cover and refrigerate until next day.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes well done.
Peel.
Mix in all ingredients.
Bake in 2 crusts at 325° for 1 hour.

title: meal in one hot dish
directions: Crumble and brown hamburger with onion. Stir in soups and water. Sprinkle with potatoes. Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in salted water to cover until tender.
Bone chicken and save broth to cook spaghetti in.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook until tender. Add mushroom soup, evaporated milk and cheese. Simmer until cheese is melted. Add chicken and soup mixture.
Pour into casserole.
Makes 3 large casseroles.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: In pan, mix fruit, nuts and raisins with 1/2 cup flour and set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir until blended.
Add applesauce to which the baking soda has been added.
Stir in flour and spices.
Mix well.
Add floured fruit and nut mixture.
Mix.
Pour into greased and floured wax paper lined pans.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork or spoon dipped in hot water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Yields 36 cookies.

title: heavenly delight salad
directions: Drain the day before to use juice in custard.

title: holiday cheeseberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add cranberry sauce and lemon juice. When cool, pour into oiled loaf pan; chill until thickened.
Whip cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream, pineapple and nuts.
Spoon mixture over gelatin.
Chill until set. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Mix until creamy.
Press onto a cookie sheet. Top with melted chocolate and cut into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: hot mustard
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl and mix thoroughly. Put into jars.

title: barbecue ham
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove garlic; add ham (about 1 pound), chipped and chopped.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together.
Use clam juice to thin it down.
Refrigerate, so the flavors will blend.

title: mexican beans and rice
directions: Put onion and water in skillet and bring to boil.
Add uncooked instant rice and reduce to simmer.
Cook for 2 minutes. Add chili beans and dry taco seasoning.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let sit for five minutes.

title: orecchiette with broccoli(little ears)
directions: Clean and wash the broccoli, having care to discard parts that are not tender.
Cook them in boiling, salted water for about 20 minutes.
Drain well; cover to keep warm.
Heat the oil in a saucepan.
Add the chopped garlic and the finely chopped anchovy.

title: green ham and eggs
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and scramble gently in hot butter.

title: cornell barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil; cook five minutes.
Cool.
Brush sauce on chicken, basting often when it's on the grill.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, coconut and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Do not beat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store on shelf.
Use heaping tablespoonful to a cup of hot water.

title: banana nog
directions: Peel and cut up banana.
Place in freezer container or bag; freeze until firm.
In a blender, combine milk, ice milk, banana and vanilla extract.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Sprinkle each serving with nutmeg.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, beat first 7 ingredients at low speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool and then top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: strawberry twinkie cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Layer in oblong dish in the following manner:
Twinkies (uncut).
Pour strawberries and juice over Twinkies.
Smooth prepared pudding over strawberries. Spread Cool Whip over pudding layer .
Better to chill for 30 minutes to 1 hour but may be served immediately.

title: breakfast before
directions: Cook bacon, drain well.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings. Layer bread, meat and cheese in 11 x 9-inch pan.
Add onion and green pepper.
Pour egg mixture over bread, meat and cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sausage bisquick balls
directions: Crumble sausage in Bisquick.
In double boiler, melt cheese and add to sausage mixture. Roll into balls. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen to use later.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Grind cranberries and add to jello mixture.
Mix well.
Grind orange and apple; add to mixture.
Add pineapple and walnuts.
Pour into an 11 x 9-inch dish and chill.
Good with a dab of mayonnaise.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together and add eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring and add to the first mixture.
Beat in part of the flour, milk and salt.
Add the remaining flour and remaining ingredients, putting the soda and vinegar in last.
Bake in layers at 350° until tested done.

title: no sugar shoney strawberry pie
directions: Combine cold water and cornstarch in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; let cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened and clear.
Remove from heat; immediately add Jell-O.
Mix well.
Let cool slightly, then add sugar substitutes.
Place the fresh strawberries into a baked pie shell (use a deep dish pie shell). After liquid has cooled to warm, pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Refrigerate.
When pie has set firmly, top with Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon treats
directions: Cover large cookie sheet with foil.
Line pan with crackers and set aside.
Put margarine and sugar in saucepan and boil 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pool hall slaw
directions: Bring ingredients to boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: oatmeal chipper cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add oil, egg and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add chocolate pieces.
The mixture is rather dry.
Add 1 teaspoon of water if batter is too dry to form cookies.
Place cookies on pan.
Recipe doubles well. Bake Time:
12 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except oyster crackers.
Stir well.
Put in airtight container.
Stir occasionally for 24 hours.

title: buttermilk braid
directions: Warm buttermilk and add lemon juice, butter, honey and salt; heat until butter melts.
Then add raisins and remove from stove. Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over the surface of the liquid and let it rise for five minutes.
With a large wooden spoon, stir the yeast in gently and allow mixture to bubble.
Stir in 1 cup flour and then mix eggs.
Add 5 more cups of flour, one cup at a time.
Knead dough on a floured surface until it is firm and elastic.
Knead 10 minutes.
Transfer to a large, greased bowl, turning so that all sides are greased.
Cover and let rise for one hour, until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and knead for one or two more minutes.
Divide dough into four pieces, making 2 slightly larger.
Divide 2 large pieces into 6 pieces.
Braid 3 pieces each. Place the smaller braid on the larger ones.
Brush with egg.
Let rise for one hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Note:
Use large mixing bowl for this.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Boil 1 minute to dissolve sugar. Add the cocoa, peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Drop on wax paper.
Let cool and set.

title: chess cake
directions: Cut cake mix, margarine and egg together until mixture is soft like dough.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat together powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs until smooth.
Pour over pressed mixture and bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: aunt agnes' caramel icing
directions: Put 2/3 cup sugar in skillet on low heat and let brown.
In heavy saucepan, combine salt, flour and sugar; mix well.
Add milk and margarine; cook on low heat until margarine is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Add browned sugar and cook 1 minute really fast (on medium-high) or until soft ball stage.
(It might take a little longer.)
Be sure to stir constantly when adding sugar and cooking. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Let cool a short time, then beat with mixer until thick.
If it gets too thick to spread, add warm milk, a teaspoon at a time.
Will ice 3 cake layers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugars, butter, milk and salt.
Cook to soft-ball stage, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows and peanut butter.
Beat until firm.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: double chocolate cookie bars
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of margarine and 24 crushed Oreo cookies.
Mix and spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine 1 full minute, set off heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla, add oats last.
Pour into ungreased pan to cool.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine or butter.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla, coconut and chopped nuts.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to mix gradually and then add Rice Krispies.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: cranberry streusel coffee cake
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; cook, stirring constantly, until berries begin to pop.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice
cucumbers;
soak
pickles in lime with one gallon water for 24 hours.
Rinse real good; soak in clear water for 2 or
3 hours.
Make
syrup
of sugar, vinegar, spices and salt. Cook slow for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Seal while hot.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Add all ingredients except vanilla wafers to whipped cream. Stir and refrigerate.
Just before serving, add vanilla wafers.

title: country muffins
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until lumps disappear.
Bake in greased pan at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: skillet balls
directions: Mix dates, sugar, oleo and egg in large iron skillet and place over low heat.
Cook until dates are melted, stirring occasionally.
Turn off heat and add rice crispies and pecans. Mix well and let cool.
Roll into small balls and roll each ball in coconut.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Prepare Minute rice.
Combine with broccoli (prepared and drained) and mushroom soup (diluted with 1 can of water).
Pour Cheez Whiz over mixture.
Mix well and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: italian sausage and bean soup
directions: Brown sausage in oil with onions. Add tomatoes (with juices) and break or cut them into large pieces. Add water, bouillon, sugar, seasoned salt, pepper, garlic powder and red pepper. Add beans.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until pasta is tender, about 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pinto beans and rotel tomatoes
directions: Sort beans, wash, cover with water and cook until done.
Put one can of Ro-Tel tomatoes and slice Polish sausage in 1 1/2 to 2 inch chunks.
Season to taste.
This is a little warm but very good.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars.
Add extracts.
Stir in eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Chill and roll into balls the size of walnuts. Flatten with glass dipped in confectioners sugar.
Decorate with sprinkles, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: magic macaroni
directions: Brown meat in oil; stir in everything, but macaroni and cheese.
Bring
to	a
boil; add macaroni.	Simmer 20 minutes; add cheese to melt.

title: chicken divan
directions: Spray round casserole with no stick spray.
Layer broccoli in bottom, then chicken.
Combine soup, lemon juice, curry and mayonnaise.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients and let set for at least 2 hours.
Fold cream and marshmallows together and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Fold all ingredients together before serving.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: 7-up prom punch
directions: Combine juices and serve when chilled.
As you serve, add cold 7-Up.
Makes 36 five ounce servings.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; gradually beat in well beaten eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Beat in mayonnaise. Toss together the remaining ingredients.
Pour on dressing.
Mix well.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Slice apples 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Mix with cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar in a large bowl and set aside.
Mix eggs, oil and 2 1/2 cups of sugar until smooth.
Add alternately to batter the dry ingredients (flour, salt and baking powder) and wet ingredients (orange juice, vanilla), starting and ending with dry ingredients.

title: me me's pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 375 degree for about 45-50 minutes.

title: green pepper tomato salad
directions: Place peppers, tomatoes, onions, olives and celery in salad bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over salad.
Toss gently; chill.

title: one dish meal
directions: Pour contents of one can of peas plus liquid into a greased baking dish.
Add one layer sliced carrots and one layer of sliced potatoes and a little onion, cut fine.
Sprinkle each layer with salt as needed (optional).

title: barb's veggy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Serve with relish tray.

title: holly bunches
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter slowly in a large saucepan.
Will scorch easily.
Add vanilla and green food coloring.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Put 2 or 3 red hots on to look like small bunches of holly.

title: german pancakes - delicate thins
directions: Leftover pancakes, no topping, can be folded and cut into very thin, noodle-like slices.
Serve as pancake soup (Pfannkuchen Suppe) by pouring any hot broth over pancake noodles.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes. Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread on baked crust.
Add chopped veggies.

title: crunchy fudge bars
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal. Mix and press half of mixture into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill in refrigerator. Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients and stir in double boiler until chocolate melts.
Spread over chilled cereal.
Spread remaining cereal over top.
Press gently.
Chill 10 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: crab salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water. Heat the tomato soup and add gelatin. Stir in cream cheese. Add salt and pepper. Add green onion, green pepper and celery. Mix in the salad dressing and crab meat. Let set 12 hours in a greased 6 x 10 inch dish.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour and sugar; slowly add milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Mix well and pour over fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine yeast in warm water.
Combine milk and 1 cup water. Scald milk before using.
Pour scalded liquid over shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir until melted.
When lukewarm, add 2 cups flour and softened yeast.
Then oats.
Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and soft, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and brush top with melted shortening.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Punch down, let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Brush with melted shortening.
Let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: oyster cracker mix
directions: Mix oil, garlic powder, dill weed and Ranch dressing in a large, airtight bowl.
Add crackers and stir every 20 minutes or until well mixed and oil is absorbed.
Keep in an airtight container for a long time.
This can be put in freezer and kept for months.

title: low-fat lemon-poppy seed cake(serves 9)
directions: Melt margarine and cool to room temperature.

title: microwave layered dinner
directions: Mix green beans, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, the croutons, mayonnaise and mustard.
Layer half each of the ham and green bean mixture in 1-quart casserole.
Repeat once.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until hot and bubbly 13 to 15 minutes.
Rotate 1/4 turn every 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese and the French fried onions.
Microwave, uncovered, at Medium-high (70%) until cheese is melted, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: un-apple pie
directions: Peel and deseed zucchini.
Slice like you would an apple. Cover zucchini with water and boil 2 minutes.
Drain and set aside to cool.
Mix all other ingredients together and stir gently through zucchini.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Squish soup mix, sausage and cheese together.
Form into balls and place in caps of mushrooms.
Cook at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Delicious.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs together.
Mix in separate bowl the flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix dry ingredients into sugar, oil and eggs mix, a small amount at a time until all mixed. Bake 1 hour at 350° in a Bundt pan or flat pan or layer pan.
Ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: graham cracker crunch
directions: Cover cookie sheet or jelly roll pan with foil.
Fill cookie sheet with as many crackers (broken into small squares) as possible.
Put sugar, vanilla and margarine in pan and boil for 2 minutes.
Add nuts to boiling mixture.
Spread over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add other ingredients. Congeal.
Make topping of sour cream, mayonnaise and marshmallows. (Equal amount of miniature marshmallow may be substituted.)
Mix well and spoon over salad when ready to serve.

title: reeses cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Stir together flour and soda. In
a large bowl, beat shortening, sugars and vanilla. Add eggs, beat well. Gradually add flour mixture. Beat well. Stir in chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit struedel
directions: Place fruit in a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with 3/4 to 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix the egg, 1 cup sugar and flour; crumble over fruit.
Sprinkle a little more cinnamon and 3/4 stick melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Cook on medium heat. Boil for 2 1/2 minutes. Drop by tablespoon onto foil-covered cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake (30 minutes in microwave; 45 minutes in a 325° oven).
Make sure beans don't get too dry.

title: plain roll dough
directions: Soften yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well.
Beat in softened yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well.
Cover and let rise in warm place (82°) until double (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Turn out on lightly floured surface and shape as desired.
Shape rolls; let double (25 to 30 minutes).
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 to 12 minutes in greased pans.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion, peas, water chestnuts and radishes in a large salad bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing layers completely.
Chill 24 hours or overnight. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Toss before serving.

title: chicken (easy does it) sauce
directions: Place the chicken pieces in a baking pan or casserole dish. Arrange onion rings on top of chicken.
Cover chicken with crushed tomatoes.
Sprinkle with basil and pepper.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup of cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except beans.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add green beans and continue to simmer 30 minutes more. Makes 6 servings.
I also add corn.

title: moravian cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, cover and let stand a week or longer in a very cool place.
Roll out dough until paper thin.
Cut out cookies and place on a greased cookie sheet and bake about 6 minutes at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, green peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt.
Cover with chipped ice.
Mix.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Remove garlic.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Bring to a boil for 6 minutes, then pack in jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: shrimp & clam dip
directions: Mix together the day before, chill. Serve with crackers.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix crackers, seeds and oleo (save about half for the top). Cover bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Combine chicken, soup and sour cream; put over crackers.	Top with extra cracker mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: light and easy curried fruit
directions: Drain apricot halves and pineapple, peaches and pears in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine reserved liquid, brown sugar and curry powder together in a small bowl; stir well.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated and bubbly.
Yield:
8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: meringue heath bar torte
directions: Beat egg whites until they peak; add sugar and cream of tartar and continue beating until all sugar is dissolved.
Spread on aluminum foil the size of a pie pan.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 250° oven.
Do not open door until hours later.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Mix Karo
syrup
and
sugar
together in a saucepan and bring to a
boil.
Boil
for
1 minute, then remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together and spread on top.

title: rye canape boat
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread.
Slice loaf of bread in half, lengthwise and scoop out inside, which can be cut into bite-size pieces for dipping.
Put filling into loaf half just before serving.

title: warm spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit and place in 11 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, cloves and allspice together and sprinkle over fruit. Dot small pieces of margarine on fruit.
Bake in microwave for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: jello dessert
directions: Make banana cream or vanilla cream as for pie filling.
Cool and pour over layer of graham crackers in bottom of pan.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Mix 2 packages jello as usual and let congeal.
Pour over top and refrigerate overnight.
Add Cool Whip, if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook desired amount of potatoes and cool.
Cut up in small pieces and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cut up butter over top and sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce over all and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until warm and slightly browned.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Pour melted margarine over Rice Krispies, brown sugar and nuts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Let cool.
Save 2/3 cup for topping.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chops and turn in flour.
Turn lightly brown. Mix potatoes, onion and soup.
Place in bottom of large casserole dish.
Lay chops on top and cover.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°. Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, peanut butter and milk in a mixing bowl and stir until smooth and tan in color.
Add 1 carton of Cool Whip to mixing bowl and fold in until blended.
Pour into 3 graham cracker pie shells and place in freezer until firm.
Top all three pies with remaining carton of Cool Whip and freeze until ready to serve.

title: salted almonds(irresistible)
directions: Rub a baking sheet with almond oil or butter.
Spread almonds on sheet and place in slow oven (200°) for 45 minutes until almonds are a pale toast color.
Have ready a sheet of kitchen paper with the salt in the middle.
Empty the almonds onto the pepper and swish them in the salt.
Gather up the corners of the paper to make a tightly fastened parcel and hide it for about 5 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add Jiffy mix last.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: honey and ranch dressing grilled tenderloins
directions: Combine garlic and soy sauce in a shallow dish.
Add tenderloins.
Cover and chill 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Stir together brown sugar, honey and oil.
Add Ranch dressing mix and stir to blend.
Grill tenderloins over medium/high heat 15 to 20 minutes or until done, turning frequently and basting with Ranch dressing/honey mixture.

title: frozen chocolate mound dessert
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish with about 1/4-inch Cool Whip.
Dip cookies, one at a time, into milk to moisten. Shake off excess milk and place on Cool Whip.
When layer complete, sprinkle with coconut.
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Can be frozen up to a week before serving.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Mix and refrigerate about 3 hours before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend sour cream, apples, pineapple, curry powder and garlic salt.
Place in bowl and chill.
Garnish with sliced apples around outer edges of bowl.
Makes 3 cups.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add milk and blend well. Mix baking powder, flour, salt and walnuts together.
Add to mixture and beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured pan(s) in a 350° oven until top springs back to touch.
When cool, spread with icing.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute green onion in oil.
Add chicken broth, milk and potatoes.
Boil; lower heat and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 12 minutes.
Add corn.
Cook 1 minute.

title: miss bank's winter squash pie
directions: Put in blender until smooth.
Pour in a deep dish pie shell in a cold oven.
Cook at 325° until firm.

title: eggplant napoli(serves 6)
directions: In a skillet, saute the chopped onions in oil.
Add the tomato puree, water, salt, marjoram, oregano and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour in 9-inch pie pan (greased).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork with rice
directions: Prepare 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Lay rice, uncooked, in pan.
Set the oven for 350°.
Dip pork chops in egg, then bread crumbs.
Lightly brown on both sides.
Prepare mushroom soup.
Add can of mushrooms.
Pour on rice in pan.
Place gently fried pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° and then 3/4 hour at 250°.

title: rumaki
directions: Drain and cut chestnuts in halves.
Rinse, drain and cut livers in half.
Sprinkle bacon strips lightly with ground cloves and brown sugar.
Place piece of liver and chestnut on one end. Roll and secure with toothpick.
Arrange on microwave-safe plate and cover with paper towel.
Microwave at High for 3 to 4 minutes. Rotate and microwave for an additional minute.
Makes 40.

title: brown sugar refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and soda. Form roll in wax paper; put in refrigerator.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Roll crackers into very fine crumbs. Beat egg whites stiff. Add the sugar. Fold in cracker crumbs with 1/2 teaspoon baking powder and pinch of salt. Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into greased pie pan and spread evenly. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Cook onions, celery and carrots in chicken broth until almost done.
Add potatoes, then cauliflower, broccoli, soups and Velveeta.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: sweet 'n sour kielbasa
directions: Brown kielbasa in skillet. Mix apricot preserves and barbecue sauce in crock-pot until mixed. Add kielbasa and pineapple to crock-pot.
Cook until done.

title: special poultry stuffing
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, green pepper, celery and pimento and saute for 1 minute.
Add pecans and toss lightly.
Add water. Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Add stuffing and mix well.
Remove from heat and cool before stuffing poultry or pork chops.
Makes enough stuffing for an 8 to 10 pound turkey or chicken.

title: eggplant vermicelli
directions: Cook vermicelli.
Drain and set aside.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Add olive oil and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add eggplant and next 5 ingredients.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add zucchini, mushrooms and tomatoes; saute 2 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated.

title: bran muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Stir in cereal.
Add buttermilk, oil and eggs and blend until moistened.
Do not stir batter again!
Store in a covered non-metal bowl in refrigerator. May be stored up to six weeks.
When needed, fill lightly greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spiced apple jam
directions: Peel, core, cut in pieces the apples.
Place 1/4 of apples and 1/2 c. water in blender on high speed for 15 seconds.
Repeat with remaining apples and water.
May use food processor.
Measure 5 cups in a large pan.
Add sugar, spices and lemon juice.
Place over high heat and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat at one and stir in Certo.
Skim off foam.
Ladle into hot jars.
Seal and treat according to current standards.
Fills approximately 10 - 8 oz. jars.

title: homemade chocolate pie
directions: It will be best if you can use a double boiler. Scald milk. Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in a separate bowl. Beat egg yolks slightly. Stir dry ingredients slowly into milk. Add some of the hot mixture and stir them. Mix all together. Cook until thick. Then add butter and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix in blender until smooth. Water may be added to reach desired consistency.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter. Press into bottom and halfway up sides of 9-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 60 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave door ajar for 30 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven, cool and then refrigerate for at least 3 hours or overnight.
When serving, top with desired topping such as cherries or strawberries.

title: congealed salad
directions: Bring Jell-O and crushed pineapple to a boil; cool.
Add Cool Whip, buttermilk, marshmallows and nuts.
Let congeal.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into greased 1-quart casserole. Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking cocoa, cinnamon, cloves and allspice in large bowl; mix well.
Mix sugar with applesauce in bowl; mix well.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in butter, pecans and raisins.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until layers test done.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Spread frosting between layers and over top and side of cake.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with combined soup and broth.
Blend flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: easy punch
directions: Prepare the Kool-Aid according to directions on package.
Add lemonade concentrate, using only 1 can of water.
Chill and, at serving, add chilled ginger ale.

title: waldorf-astoria cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring (use 1 small bottle and add enough water to measure 1/4 cup of liquid) and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk alternately with sifted flour and salt. Add vanilla.
Dissolve soda in vinegar (hold over bowl as it will foam).
Blend mixture into cake batter.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch or 9-inch cake pans and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool.
Cut each portion in half horizontally with heavy thread and ice.

title: meat and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown beef. Slice potatoes. Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a buttered baking dish and bake at 350° until thoroughly cooked.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Do not cut up.
Cover chicken with water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt per pound of chicken, pepper, onion and parsley.
Boil 1 1/2 hours until chicken starts coming off the bones.
Remove chicken and remove meat from bones after it cools.
Mix flour, baking powder, dash of salt, shortening and milk to make dough.
Mix well.
Roll dough thin and cut into 1 x 1-inch strips.
Drop into hot boiling broth.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and add chicken.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve hot.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and make into meatballs.
Do not fry. Place the meatballs in a large casserole dish.
In a separate dish combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour the sauce over the meatballs and cook at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Delicious served on mashed potatoes.

title: biscuits on creamy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat in a saucepan the peas, chicken, soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper just to boiling.
Pour chicken mixture into ungreased, oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place biscuits on cheese.
Bake until biscuits are brown, about 20 minutes.

title: cookies
directions: Do not mix.
Melt the oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the crushed graham crackers, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts, then dribble the condensed milk on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Cut when cool.

title: herbed garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cut each potato into quarters. Place in a microwave-safe 9-inch square baking dish. Combine butter, garlic, parsley, seasoned salt and paprika in a small bowl and mix well. Pour evenly over potatoes. Microwave on HIGH, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes. Bake in oven until golden, about 6 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked chicken
directions: Cut breasts in half.
Place bacon pieces under skin.
Line baking pan with foil.
Combine soup, sauce, melted butter and 1/4 of onion soup mix.
Dip breast in mixture.
Place skin side up in pan.
Pour sherry over.
Sprinkle on Accent.
Spoon remaining soup mixture over.
Sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Baste once.

title: quick and easy oreo pie
directions: Crumble cookies and layer the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan.
Soften the ice cream and layer on top of cookies (1/2 to 1-inch thick). Pour chocolate syrup over to cover completely.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Freeze before serving.

title: baked fajitas casserole
directions: Brush chicken with canola oil or butter and broil on each side.
After broiling, cut chicken into strips.
Dice green pepper and onion and saute in butter, then mix into the chicken strips. Grease the bottom of a casserole dish and layer tortillas, chicken mixture, salsa and cheese.
Repeat layers until you run out of chicken mixture.
Top with tortillas, then grated cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients.
Beat in the flour and soda, mixing well.
Finally, mix in the mashed bananas.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Chill until jelled.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit in colander covered in refrigerator 1 1/2 days. Prepare 1 or 2 hours before serving.
Mix sour cream, marshmallows and coconut (save a handful of coconut for the top of salad from cup).
Add the fruit.
Cover the top with coconut.
Place maraschino cherries on the top of the salad.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift dry ingredients; add gradually.
Add nuts and dates.
Fill two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until butter melts.
Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch
baking
dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over
chicken.
Bake
uncovered at 325° for one hour or until tender.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove stem area and inside of green pepper.
Parboil green pepper for 10 minutes in salted water (enough to cover).
Mix remaining ingredients well and stuff peppers.
Place peppers in individual baking dishes to catch juices and bake, uncovered, 1 hour and 15 minutes in 325° preheated oven.
Baking dishes can be put on a large cookie sheet for easier handling.
Parboiling peppers improves flavor, but doesn't interfere with the baking process.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Combine all. Bake 25 minutes.

title: hot cracker spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, onion, dried beef, milk and green pepper.
Spread in a pie plate.
Saute pecans in the butter, then spread on top of mixture in pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers or Fritos.
May be prepared a day ahead and baked later.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and core apples.
Cut each apple into 8 equal pieces.
Open rolls and lay out flat.
You will have 8 pieces.
Cut each piece longways in half, making 16 pieces. Melt butter in a 10-inch pan.
Roll apple slices in dough pieces, starting with narrowest end.
Lay in pan, seam side down. Sprinkle sugar, which has been mixed with cinnamon, over wrapped apples.
Toss in some raisins, if desired.
Pour orange juice over all, then bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Beat in sugar, salt, flour, rind and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each is added.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 12 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 55 minutes.
Let cool several hours.
Chill.
Top with strawberry sauce and serve.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add mayonnaise to make moist. Refrigerate overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and milk and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring to keep from burning.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour onto a buttered sheet pan and let cool.
Cut into bars.

title: aunt irma's chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder. Add cocoa to dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add boiling water last.
Pour into two 8-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let all ingredients come to room temperature.
Mix.
Chill after forming 2 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix together yeast, sugar and water; add flour and salt and let rise 1 hour until double in size.
Roll out into rectangle; cut into narrow strips 3 1/8-inches wide.
Fold over and twist; roll in butter on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme or Parmesan cheese, garlic salt or sesame seed; let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Put all in bowl and mix well.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Keeps 10 days in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter & corn flake bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13 inch pan.
Crush corn flakes.
In medium heat, melt butter.
Add sugar and syrup. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Spread into pan. Cut in squares after cooled.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to full boil.
Cream cheese together with jello.
Add to pineapple and sugar.
Stir until dissolved. Remove from heat; add water and nuts.
Refrigerate until jello starts to mold.
Whip Dream Whip and fold in.
(I double this recipe when I use it.
This salad keeps well in the refrigerator.)

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Steam shells about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients using only one-half can of soup.
Mix well.
Fill peppers with stuffing.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour remaining half of soup over peppers.
Return to oven and continue baking 15 minutes.
Serves 4.
Fill the halves and bake them uncovered.

title: basic mayonnaise
directions: Combine eggs, salt, mustard, paprika, vinegar, sugar and 1/2 cup oil in blender.
Blend together until mixed.
Without turning off, pour remaining oil in slowly, using spatula to keep mixture flowing into blades.
Can add to mixture horseradish and Ranch salad dressing mix.

title: brandy lemonade
directions: Blend with ice cubes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in upper part of double boiler. Add milk and egg yolks; cook until thick.
Add vanilla and coconut. Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake until brown.
(You may omit coconut and vanilla and add juice of two lemons and 1 teaspoon grated lemon rind to make a lemon cream pie.)

title: hot berry cider
directions: In large saucepan, combine apple cider, raspberries, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain through cheesecloth.
Float an apple wedge in each cup.
Makes 16 (4 ounce) servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in sugar, syrup and salt, then stir in butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Pour entire bottle of Italian dressing over the warm spaghetti.
Add the chopped vegetables and the full bottle of Salad Supreme seasoning.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
The longer it sets, the better it tastes.

title: cherry cheese delight
directions: Combine margarine and crumbs.
Press into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine softened cream cheese, 1 cup confectioners sugar, milk and 1 teaspoon almond extract; mix well. Spread on graham crust.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: beef stew
directions: Put everything in one baking dish with cover.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours.
Be sure to stir periodically to be sure the meat isn't drying out.
Serve with boiled potatoes, mashed potatoes, noodles and rice.
Bake only in oven, not crock-pot.

title: jacky's pancakes
directions: Separate 4 eggs and beat separately.
Add milk to egg yolks. Add dry ingredients and butter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto hot griddle.
Turn only once.
They will cook quickly.
Serve with melted butter and maple syrup.
This is the most delicious pancake recipe ever!
You can eat them faster than I can cook them!

title: dan's pizza crust dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil, salt and mix in flour. Knead and spread into pizza pan that has been oiled lightly.
Let dough rise for 20 minutes.
Apply sauce, toppings and cheese. Bake pizza in 450° oven until done, approximately 20 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Unwrap caramels.
Melt caramels and butter together; add milk. Stir well.

title: creamy cucumber dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir well. Cover and chill.
Serve over salad greens.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together, then add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and pour into 2 layers.
Bake as directed.
Combine cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar for frosting.
Slice bananas between cake and sprinkle pecans over them.

title: special pie crust
directions: Blend together flour, salt and lard until particles are the size of small peas.
Beat egg in an 8 ounce measuring cup.
Add vinegar and mix well, then fill remainder of cup with cold milk. Mix with flour mixture.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs slightly in bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Place in loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Pat evenly to make smooth top.
Bake 1 hour. Drain off fat.
Turn out of pan.

title: eight vegetable relish(my mother called this:  hayden salad)
directions: Combine first
ingredients
in
a large mixing bowl; add salt, mixing well.
Cover and let stand in a cool place 12 to 18 hours.
Drain well and set aside.

title: easy cincinnati chili
directions: Brown beef with onions and garlic.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, chili powder, cocoa, cinnamon and allspice.
Simmer while cooking spaghetti or preparing hotdogs.
Cincinnati chili is served with spaghetti or on hotdogs to make it "Two Way."
Add cheddar cheese on top and you have "Three Way."
With chopped onions you have "Four Way" and with beans you have "Five Way." Season with Tabasco to your liking.

title: christmas spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in covered container.
To 1 cup hot water, add 1 heaping tablespoonful of mix.
Makes 1 1/2-quarts of dry mix.

title: onion soup
directions: Heat stock in soup kettle.
Slice onions.
Saute them until well done (20 minutes).
Stir constantly.
Add sauteed onions and seasoning to hot stock.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: japanese cake
directions: Stir butter to soften.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla. Sift together baking powder, flour and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Blend in raisins and candied cherries.

title: easy upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in bottom of an 8 or 9-inch skillet.
Spread 3/4 cup brown sugar over butter and spoon crushed pineapple on sugar. Prepare contents of 1 layer cake mix as directed on box and pour over pineapple.
Bake in center of oven at 350° until done.

title: grilled dry ribs and sauce
directions: Combine salt and peppers; rub mixture all over ribs.
Let ribs stand in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Bring to room temperature before cooking.
Soak wood chips for 30 minutes.
Prepare a medium-hot fire in a covered charcoal grill.
Push coals to one side.
Just before cooking, toss 1/2 of the wood chips onto the coals.
Grill ribs on the side of the grill away from the coals. Turn about every 30 minutes.
Add remaining wood chips after 45 minutes.
Cook until ribs are crusty on the outside and tender on the inside, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with Rib Sauce (follows).

title: shrimp spread
directions: Soften gelatine in water.
Boil undiluted soup; add gelatine and water.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add celery, onion and shrimp.
Add mayo and cream cheese last.
Mix well; turn into mold and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients well. Drop in hot grease. Fry until golden brown.

title: vanilla torte
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, butter and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Press in 13 x 9-inch pan to form crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° and cool.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 container Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust.
Make vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk and spread over cheese.
Make pistachio pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk and spread over vanilla pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate and enjoy!

title: easy wassail
directions: Heat the apple juice on stove top or in coffee pot.
Place red hots directly in apple juice to melt.
If using a large coffeemaker, place red hots in basket and let the apple juice perk over until melted.

title: mom's sweet and sour ribs
directions: Place ribs in single layer in pan.
Broil on all sides until well browned, drain grease.
Combine other ingredients in saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour over ribs.
Bake uncovered at 325 degrees for 1 1/2 hours or until sauce has thickened.
Spoon sauce over ribs frequently while baking.

title: breast of chicken magnifque
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Remove.
Brown mushrooms.
Stir in soup, garlic and seasonings.
Add chicken.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir now and then.
Blend in cream; heat slowly.
Serve with rice; wild rice even better.
Garnish with toasted, slivered almonds.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. May be frozen before baking. I thaw it before baking. Serves 8 to 12.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add beaten egg and milk; mix well.
Batter should be thick enough to hold shape when dropped from spoon.
Drop by teaspoon on top of hot soup. Delicious with soup beans.

title: saffron buns
directions: *Let saffron stand in water 1 hour before making the buns.

title: corn and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Place in bottom of ungreased casserole dish.
Put sliced potatoes on top of meat.
In smal bowl, mix creamed corn and milk.
Pour on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs over top.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: candy apples
directions: Wash and dry apples.

Stick wooden sticks into stem of apples. Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and butter in a deep saucepan. Cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly. Continue cooking until a small amount of syrup becomes slightly brittle in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and coloring.
Dip apples one at a time into syrup.
Work quickly. Cool on wax paper or buttered plate.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Put bacon on top of beans and push into beans.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours or until juice in beans starts to set.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: low-fat chicken and peppers
directions: Slice chicken breasts into thin strips and mix together with the next 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cut peppers and mushrooms into thin slices.
In 2 tablespoons diet margarine, cook peppers and mushrooms 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from liquid. Using the same skillet, add 2 tablespoons diet margarine.
Cook chicken mixture, stirring constantly, until meat is done.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add water and heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Serve with rice.
Yum!

title: yellow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans or a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt thoroughly.
Mix in fat, eggs, vanilla and 1/2 milk; beat 2 minutes at medium speed, then add remaining milk and beat another 2 minutes longer.
Pour batter in pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until cake surface springs back.
Cool on cake rack for a few minutes.
Remove from pan.
Frost with frosting of your choice.

title: kids' dogs
directions: Cut each wiener in thirds.
Take each biscuit and flatten slightly and spread with mustard.
Wrap each wiener piece in a biscuit; pinch to seal.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour half of mixture in large pan and let congeal.
Spread small carton sour cream over congealed mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over cream.
Congeal.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour in freezer.
Follow directions for your freezer.

title: beef macaroni bake
directions: Brown burger and onion.
Mix together; top with cheese that is leftover.
Bake on 350° for 45 minutes or until heated.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Arrange well
drained
