fruit in large baking dish.
Mix cornstarch with
reserved juices.
Melt butter in saucepan and add brown
sugar,
juice mixture and curry.
Stir, constantly, over low heat
until consistency is about that of a thin cream sauce. Pour
over	fruit.	Add
pecans.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked chicken(like kentucky fried chicken)
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a plastic bag and shake to mix. Use just amount needed.
Makes enough for a couple of times. Shake cut up chicken in this mix.
Melt 1/4 pound of butter in a shallow pan.
Arrange shook up chicken in the pan in a single layer.
Drizzle more melted butter over chicken and bake in 350° oven until done; turn once.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Put 1/2 pepper and 1/2 vinegar in blender; process until liquified. Repeat with remaining pepper and vinegar. Combine liquified pepper and vinegar with sugar in large saucepot and boil slowly for 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Add liquid pectin and boil hard for one minute. Skim and add a few drops green food coloring. Pour into jars, leaving 1/2 inch from top. Wipe jar tops and put on lids.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except grated cheese and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with grated cheese about 10 minutes before casserole is done.
Continue cooking until cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal boonies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat oil and brown sugar with an electric mixer until well blended.
Add whole wheat flour, applesauce, oats, bran, milk powder, eggs, soda, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and cloves.
Beat on low speed until combined.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spray a baking sheet with nonstick spray coating.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 to 3 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Spread dough so each cookie is about 2 inches across.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes or until set.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.
Calories:
80; Fat:

title: cranberry tea bread
directions: Combine ingredients, adding nuts last.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 400° (hot) oven 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° (moderate) and continue to bake 30 to 35 minutes.
(Filling should be slightly less set in the center than around edges.)

title: mother's black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and cook (diced) in salted water until tender. Drain and mash.
Add butter, milk, crumbs, onion, eggs and spices. Mix well.
Pour into well-oiled baking dish and cover with cheese (takes about 1/4 cup of grated cheese).
Bake in oven at 400° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli as directed, omitting salt; drain thoroughly. Place cuts into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Stir soup and grated cheese together.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg to soup mixture; stir until blended.
Pour over broccoli. Combine bread crumbs and melted margarine; sprinkle evenly over soup mixture.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes until crumbs are lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine sugar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Beat egg; add melted butter and cream. Mix well. Add vinegar very slowly while cooking over hot water, stirring all the while until mixture thickens. Chill. Toss dressing with shredded cabbage. Sprinkle with the paprika.

title: grandma myslinski's tube pan bread
directions: Stir to dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Add the milk, sugar, eggs, oleo and flour.
Beat down and pour into greased tube pan.
Let rise until 1-inch from top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: raspberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice cream, walnuts, pineapple, orange juice and banana.
Stir until ice cream melts. Then pour mixture into a mold and refrigerate until firm.
For two Pyrex dishes, make 3 recipes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and tear into small pieces.
Reserve 1/4 cup of broth.
In a casserole dish, mix Cheez Whiz and soup until smooth. Add rice, peas, mushrooms, onion and chicken pieces.
Add broth to moisten.
Mix well and top with Cheddar cheese (optional).
Top with French fried onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam or grease.
Put bread in.
Layer meat and cheese.
Beat egg, milk and seasonings.
Pour this mixture over meat and cheese.

title: pasta fruit salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook egg mixture over hot water until it begins to thicken.
Let cool.

title: hawaiian fudge
directions: Cook sugars, pineapple, ginger and cream over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil to soft ball stage (236° to 238°).
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Add butter, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan and mark into squares before cold.

title: broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in bite size pieces.
Chop onions.
Combine mayo, sugar and Parmesan cheese for dressing. Mix all together.
Chill.

title: horseradish meat loaf
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Form beef mixture into a loaf and place in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Combine catsup, brown sugar, horseradish and mustard in a small bowl.
Spoon half of catsup mixture over top of meat loaf.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Spoon remaining catsup mixture over top of meat loaf and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: gelatin punch
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Add the sugar and stir until the sugar dissolves, but do not boil.
Add the cold water and let the mixture cool, but not congeal.
Pour into a punch bowl and add the cranberry juice.
Add the ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 12.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Separate biscuits; cut in halves.
Place 1/2 slice cheese on each biscuit.
Place wiener on cheese, wrap biscuit around wiener.
Place on baking sheet with connecting point of wrap on bottom.
Cook according to instructions on biscuit can.

title: appetizers
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients.
Spread mixture about 1/2 tablespoon on each slice of beef.
Fold or roll and fasten with a toothpick.
Serve chilled.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut logs
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg.
Stir in dates, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into coconut and shape into logs. Bake until light brown, approximately 10 minutes, at 350°.

title: grilled fish
directions: In a bowl combine the lime juice, 1 tablespoon oil, ginger, cayenne pepper and enough freshly ground pepper to suit your taste. Marinate the fish in the marinade for 55 to 60 minutes.
Turn steaks 2 to 3 times.
Have grill prepared with white coals and brush the grill with remaining one tablespoon oil.
Grill the fish, brushing several times with the marinade until cooked through. Yield 4 serving.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 30 g, fat 8 g, calories 205.

title: praline strips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line cookie sheet with Club crackers. In medium saucepan, heat butter and brown sugar to boiling. Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add pecans and vanilla. Stir in. Pour over crackers. Bake 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add sliced peaches.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: flounder casserole
directions: Thaw flounder in oven.
Line bottom of casserole with flounder and smooth shrimp soup on top.
Melt margarine, adding a dash of Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce to taste and pour over crackers. Put this mixture on top of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 cup water. Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until clear.
Cool completely (may refrigerate).
Beat egg whites with salt until they form peaks.
Stir in cooled cornstarch mixture.
Beat until creamy, then add 6 tablespoons sugar one at a time and mix thoroughly.

title: creamy potato balls
directions: Peel potatoes; chop roughly.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and mash until smooth.
Beat cream cheese and softened butter until smooth.
Add milk and eggs, beat together. Add mashed potatoes to cream cheese mixture and beat until smooth. Chop bacon, saute in frying pan for 2 minutes; add to potato mixture with chopped shallots.
Cool mixture.
Form tablespoons of mixture into balls.
Coat lightly with flour, dip in combined beaten extra egg and milk and coat with breadcrumbs.
Coat again with egg and milk mixture and breadcrumbs.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Boil asparagus in salted water for 10 minutes.
Make a white sauce of the milk, butter, flour and salt.
Add grated cheese. Drain asparagus.
Pour sauce over it.
Add crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Boil sugar and 2 quarts water about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together the next 5 ingredients.
Add the sugar water.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale and ice.
I put some of the punch in containers with some orange slices and cherries and freeze them, then add them to the punch.
It makes it look very pretty.

title: cranberry relish
directions: About 5 hours before serving or day ahead, coarsely chop cranberries and apples.
Place in large bowl.
Coarsely grate peel from oranges.
Cut off white membrane; chop oranges.
Add orange peel and chopped oranges to cranberry mixture.
Stir in walnuts, orange marmalade, raisins and brown sugar.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Serve as an accompaniment to roast meats, poultry or sandwiches.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and cheese and place in	casserole
dish.
Put
onion
rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs, stir in water, ketchup, soup mix and meat.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: waldorf salad mold
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling and add Jell-O.
Stir and chill until almost set.
Add softened cream cheese, apples and grapes to Jell-O; blend.
Fold in Cool Whip, celery and nuts.
Pour into mold; refrigerate.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin-pecan pie
directions: Mix
brown
sugar,
flour,
spices
and salt.
Beat egg yolks; add
milk	and stir into first mixture.
Cook over hot water until
thick, stirring constantly.	Add pumpkin, butter or margarine
and 3/4 cup pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made of egg whites and sugar. Garnish with
remaining pecans.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) for 20 minutes.
Serve cold.

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix sugar and Kool-Aid in cold water and add to gelatin mixture, then add pineapple juice and chill.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Put into pot sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo and bring to a boil. Boil high for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Take off heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well and pour out on wax or foil-covered cookie sheet.
Place in refrigerator until set (about 1 hour).
Cut into pieces and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: penuche(butterscotch fudge)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in heavy pot over medium-low heat. Add brown sugar; heat to boiling.
Add sugar, pinch of salt and sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves and mixture reaches soft ball stage (236°).
Cool at room temperature until lukewarm (110°).
Do not stir.
Beat until mixture holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour juice and water into bottom of percolator.
Place sugar and spices in top of percolator and perk until done.

title: broccoli chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine soup and milk; set aside.
Combine chicken, broccoli, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can of onions.
Stir in 3/4 cup soup mixture evenly between the tortillas.
(Bake covered at 350°.) Roll up the tortillas and place seam side down in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir tomato into the remaining soup and pour over the top of tortillas.
Bake covered for 35 minutes.
Top each tortilla with remaining cheese and onions; uncover and continue baking 5 minutes longer.

title: salad dessert
directions: Mix the dry jello with cottage cheese and add Cool Whip. Drain oranges real good and add.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine melted margarine and Oreos.
Press in bottom and 1-inch up sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add whipping cream; blend well.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes or until center is set.
(To minimize cracking, place shallow pan half full of hot water on lower oven rack during baking.)
Cool.

title: andy's hot chip dip
directions: Option:
Use mild cheese if too spicy!

title: layered dessert
directions: Make a crust of crushed vanilla wafers.
Sprinkle with sugar for sweetness.
Melt butter and pour over crust as even as possible.
Pour prepared pudding on top of crust.
Pour prepared pie filling over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas; add eggs. Add flour, sifted with sugar, salt and soda. Add nuts. Stir well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Pour in casserole bowl.
Mix cheese and sour cream. Spread cheese mixture on top of ground beef.
Layer crescent rolls on top.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: almond cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 2 ingredients.
Add flour and almonds.
Mix well.
Knead dough gently for 1/2 minute.
Form 1-inch balls.
Flatten balls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine water and jello.
Add cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Spread over jello mixture.

title: texas sheet cake and frosting
directions: Bring to boil the first 3 ingredients; put in mixing bowl and add next 3 ingredients and beat.
Add the next 3 ingredients and pour out on greased large (at least 18 x 12 inches) sheet with edge.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix together sour cream and baking soda.
Add to mixture along with remaining ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan or mini loaf pans.

title: tuna imperial
directions: Separate tuna meat.
Combine with eggs, bread crumbs, pimento, green pepper, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and butter.

title: red berry salad
directions: Mix water and jello in blender for 1 minute.
Add bananas and blend 30 seconds.
Add strawberries and blend well.
Stir in crushed pineapple by hand.
Pour into mold.
Chill until set. Serves 8.

title: pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Cream Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread 1/2 on pretzel crust (reserve other 1/2 for top).
Drain pineapple. Cook pineapple juice and 2 tablespoons cornstarch, stirring constantly; boil until thick.
Let cool.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and pineapple.
Spread on Cool Whip mixture and top with remaining Cool Whip mixture.

title: kelly's picnic salad
directions: Cut up vegetables. Pour dressing over them.
Mix and cover. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: fruity jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in bananas, strawberries and pineapple; mix well. Transfer to a 2-quart serving bowl. Refrigerate until firm. Makes 9 servings.

title: the world's best - mama's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugars (white and brown) until light and fluffy.
Add egg, then oil and mix well after each addition.
Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and pecans, stirring well.
Then add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Form balls teaspoon size with dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Allow to cook a few minutes before moving.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen, depending on size.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Stir well and let cool.
Mix together brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in dates and water.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir in sugar and date mixture.
Blend in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In an 8 x 8-inch baking dish, layer hamburger.
Sprinkle taco seasoning over hamburger.
Spread refried beans on top of hamburger and seasoning.
Mix sour cream and taco sauce and layer on top of beans.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: grilled steak strips
directions: Cut steak crosswise into 3 x 1/8-inch strips when partially frozen.
Combine ingredients in freezer bag.
Add steak. Refrigerate 3 to 24 hours.
Turn and squeeze several times while marinating.
Thread steak on 4 skewers.
Grill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Prepare peppers by removing top and seeds. Cook in enough boiling water to cover for 5 minutes. Cook and stir hamburger and onion until light brown. Drain off grease.
Stir in garlic salt, rice and most of the tomato sauce.
Stuff peppers with hamburger mixture.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Pour rest of tomato sauce over them. Cover and cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and cook 15 more minutes. Sprinkle with cheese on top.

title: peach blitz torte
directions: To egg yolks, add enough water to make 1/2 cup plus two tablespoons.
Combine with cake mix and beat 4 minutes.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Spread meringue on unbaked cake layers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool layer meringue side up.
Spread 2/3 whipped cream over cake; arrange 2/3 of well drained peaches on cream.
Place second layer on top.
Spoon remaining cream and arrange peaches on top of cake.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine meat, seasonings, milk and oats.
Shape into 20 balls and brown on all sides in Crisco.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add enough water to bring to desired consistency.
Place meatballs in casserole dish and pour sauce over top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab mold
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into jello mold or glass dish.
Serve when well set.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: If in a hurry, a good Italian salad dressing is tasty!

title: mystery potatoes
directions: Mix; spread in a 3-quart buttered shallow casserole.
Serves 8.
Bake, uncovered,
11/2 hours at 325° or 1 hour at 350° or 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together and shape into balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: mexico chiquto salsa
directions: Drain tomatoes.
Save 1/2 cup juice.
Blend tomatoes in blender.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg with onion; drain.
Put hamburg and all other ingredients in large kettle; cook until done.

title: black truffle frittata
directions: Beat the eggs with a little salt and pepper in a bowl.
Stir in potatoes, truffle and Prosciutto.

title: grandmother's sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs and beat thoroughly.
Dissolve soda in boiling water in a large cup.
Fill to the 1-cup mark with buttermilk.
This will foam up and may run over so use a pint-measuring cup.
Sift the salt, baking powder and nutmeg with two cups of flour.
Add the flavoring and enough flour to make a stiff dough (usually 4 or 5 cups).
Chill the dough overnight.

title: sauerkraut bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough; let rise.
Fry sauerkraut and desired amount of kielbasa in butter, adding water as needed to steam. Cook until dry before using.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll out 1 loaf bread on floured surface.
Place in baking pan, turning up edges on sides.
Put a layer of sauerkraut and kielbasa in pan.
Roll out second loaf; wrap around rolling pin and cover mixture.
Pinch edges to seal.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and chopped peanuts in a large bowl; set aside.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: In baking dish, mix melted butter with flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 15 minutes, then set aside to cool.

title: quick and easy pie
directions: Put berries in a bowl.
Pour sugar and cornstarch over berries.
Lightly combine ingredients together; pour mixture into one of the pie shells.
Place other pie shell upside down over pie shell and berry mixture and remove its pan.
Cook at 400° for approximately 40 minutes, or until brown.

title: low country shrimp boil
directions: Boil water.
Add shrimp spice, garlic, salt and lemon; mix. Keep on rapid boil.
Add potatoes and sausage; cook until done, then add corn.
Last, add shrimp.
Cook for about 3 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat; drain water.
Serve.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes(great party treat for kids)
directions: Preheat oven according to cake directions.
Line cupcake tins with cupcake liners.
Mix cake batter according to box directions, then pour mixture into ice cream cones, about 1/2 full, and place in each cupcake liner.
Bake as usual according to cupcake time on box.
When baked, let cool, then ice with frosting.
Garnish with colored sprinkles.
When done, looks just like ice cream cones. Easy for kids to eat and no cleanup.
The paper liners keep the cones from burning during baking.

title: country ham with red eye gravy
directions: Fry ham until done.
Take ham out of pan then put black coffee into the hot grease in bowl.
Stir around. Put sugar on after you get gravy onto plate.
Sop with hot biscuit or Grandma's hot hoecake, made like biscuit dough, poured in a big black frying pan and baked in oven.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Place fresh shelled nuts
in
shallow
pan.
Set pan in warm, not hot, oven (300°)
until nuts are dry.
Do not brown. Boil pint jars 5 minutes.
Invert to drain dry.
Pack hot nuts into jars, leaving
1/2 inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process pints 10 minutes at 5 pound pressure.
If you prefer, nuts may be processed in boiling
water
bath
for 20 minutes.
Let the water in canner stand well below the tops of the jars.

title: taco layer dip
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients.
Spread in bottom of large, low bowl.
Chop all other ingredients and layer in order.
Serve with lots of tortilla chips.

title: cheryl jensen's rolls
directions: Melt margarine with sugar and salt in water (melt margarine with minimal heat--hot tap water is okay).
Cool if necessary.
Add yeast and dissolve.
Let mixture stand 15 minutes.
Add beaten eggs, baking powder and flour; mix well.
Let rise for 45 minutes to 1 hour until doubled.
Form balls.
Bake at 350° until bottom is light brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake 1 tray at a time.
Makes 42 rolls.
These rolls are extremely light.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and egg yolks.
Add Pet milk and cook until thick.
Add butter, vanilla and eggs, beaten.
Pour into baked pie shell and bake in 425° oven until brown, about 6 minutes.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Mix all together, except barbecue sauce.
Cover both sides of meat with mixture.
Wrap in foil and place in baking pan.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 5 hours in 300° oven. Sometimes I put it in to cook at bedtime and cook it for 12 to 14 hours at 200°.
Uncover top of meat for the last 30 minutes and add the barbecue sauce at this time.

title: delightful kielbasa
directions: Slice the kielbasa into 1/2 inch slices.
Brown in a skillet over medium heat for 3-4 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Put potatoes in bowl and microwave on high for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, sauerkraut, apples, water, salt and pepper to skillet. Mix well. Bring to a boil.
Lower to medium heat. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until apples and potatoes are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add some Hungarian paprika before serving.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk and water.
Add sugar, salt, egg and shortening.
Add 3 cups flour.
Beat.
Gradually add remaining flour; turn dough out on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; brush top with soft shortening.
Cover.
Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Shape rolls and place on greased baking sheet and let rise again until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: great potato soup
directions: Cube potatoes.
Chop onion.
Crumble fried bacon.
Chop ham. Place in pot.
Add water to cover potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are starting to get soft.
Add salt, pepper, mushroom soup and milk.
Add remainder of water.
Simmer until done.
More water can be added for personal preference of consistency.
Thicken with 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 1/2 cup water.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: little smokies
directions: For each pound of little Smokies, cover with one jar Heinz chili sauce in crock-pot.
Cook for at least 1 hour on low.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Make Crust:
Combine crumbs, brown sugar and melted butter. Mix well.
Press with bottom of tablespoon into bottom and sides of an 8-inch square pan.
Chill one hour.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour and beat well.
Add eggs and Crisco and beat.
Add remaining flour.
Knead until smooth.
Cover, let rise until double.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken in strips or McNuggets.
Dip chicken pieces in this order:
Parmesan cheese, beaten eggs and bread crumbs.
Heat oil in a frying pan on medium-high heat.
Fry until golden brown and no longer pink inside.
After chicken is cooked, let drain on paper towels.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Place in a deep casserole dish (1 to 2-inches extra room to rise).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on dish depth.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Put butter, curry powder and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Melt to a syrup.
Arrange half the fruit in the bottom of an ovenproof casserole dish.
Pour in half the almonds and half the syrup. Arrange the rest of the fruit on top and add remaining syrup and almonds.
Garnish the top with the maraschino cherries.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Can be assembled the day before.
Ready to be heated anytime.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: souper tuna crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kolaches
directions: Flatten biscuits.
Place meat and cheese in center and wrap biscuit around and seal edges.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: little pizzas
directions: Combine ingredients; spread on crackers.
Place in preheated 350° oven for approximately 5 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: aunt lou ann's vegetable pizza
directions: Cover bottom of buttered jelly roll pan with crescent rolls; pinch together perforations.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (10 minutes).
Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread on baked crescent rolls.
Spread vegetables on; top with cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine and mix well. Store in an airtight container.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately. Add flavoring and red food coloring.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan at 325°.

title: macaroon bars
directions: Sprinkle 1 1/2 c. coconut into well greased 13x9x2 baking pan.
Combine milk and almond extract and drizzle 1/2 over coconut. Unroll crescent dough and arrange in a single layer over coconut.
Drizzle with remaining milk mixture and sprinkle
with remaining coconut.
Bake at 350° 30-35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool before cutting.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields three dozen.

title: sweet potato apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour a 9x5x3 inch loaf pan. In a large bowl, combine the butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla extract, sweet potatoes and apple butter. Beat until well mixed.
Gradually add the flour and beat until mixed.
Stir in pecans. Pour into prepared loaf pan and bake for about 55 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of bread.
Turn out of pan immediately after removing from oven.

title: key west garbanzo soup
directions: Cook onion, garlic and green pepper in shortening.
Add chorizos.
Add garbanzos, water, tomato sauce and salt.
Cook until garbanzos start to soften. Add potatoes and cabbage. Cook until done.

title: joyce's baked beans
directions: Cook beans in salt and water until tender.
Do not drain water.
In the meantime, cook bacon.
Remove from pan.
Dice onion and saute in bacon grease.
Add bacon and onions to the cooked tender beans.
Add brown sugar, molasses and dry mustard.
Cover and cook in 300° oven for 4 hours.

title: french pear pie
directions: Combine pears and lemon juice.
Combine sugar, 1/3 cup flour and ginger.
Add these two mixes, plus Karo, then raisins.
Spoon into unbaked shell.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the Karo, sugar and butter; heat until butter is melted and sugar dissolved.
Do not boil.
Beat the eggs and to them add the cooked mixture.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Drop the pecans in a few at a time.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: country cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl, mixing well.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Add to dry mixture and stir with wooden spoon until just moistened.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Edges should be golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 16 squares.
Serve warm or cool.

title: chicken and vegetable supper soup
directions: Simmer broth and rice 10 minutes.
Add all vegetables except zucchini; simmer 10 minutes more.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water per package instructions. Drain and arrange in shallow baking dish.
Simmer chicken in small amount of water for 35 minutes.
Drain and arrange on broccoli. Mix next 3 ingredients.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot cider-cranberry punch
directions: Put cider, cranberry juice, cinnamon, cloves and orange peel into a large pot.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 25 to 35 minutes.
Line a strainer with cheesecloth and strain punch.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons of rum into each mug, then fill to the rim with hot punch.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl at one time. (They need not be at room temperature.) Beat at medium speed for 10 minutes. Stir occasionally to insure shortening is not holding onto beaters. Bake 65 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crock-pot barbecue chicken
directions: Dip chicken in flour and brown slightly in skillet.
Put in crock-pot on high and pour a moderate amount of barbecue sauce over chicken.
Reduce heat and cook 4 to 6 hours on low.

title: ranch roundups
directions: Combine salad dressing mix and mayonnaise; spread thin layer on sliced bread.
Top each pieces with a few shreds of cheese and thinly sliced vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until crispy.
Yields 25 appetizers.

title: pink salad
directions: Whip milk and Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients and mix well.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, baking soda and pudding together. Set aside. Blend sugars, margarine and eggs. Slowly add flour mixture. Mix in oatmeal, then chocolate chips. Drop onto cookie sheets and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: hot cocoa
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together sugar and cocoa powder. Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Heat over medium heat until warm.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Make stuffing as directed on box.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer one recipe stuffing, then chicken, followed by combined soups and top with stuffing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for one hour.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat all well.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat eggnog
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Yields 4 (5 ounce) servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Combine eggs, oil and berries and add to dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: sugared pecans or peanuts
directions: Combine sugar, water and butter.
Boil until syrup will spin a thread.
Pour
in 2 cups pecan halves or raw peanuts and stir constantly until syrup begins to harden.
Pour out on cookie sheet and separate.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 300° for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Allow to cool.

title: granny's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan. Add water as needed to thin down sauce or make more. Stir until hot. Great over chicken!!!

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box, using pineapple juice for liquid.
Add water to make proper amount as called for. Bake as directed, using well-greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool cake in pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in egg. Mix pineapple and pecans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: charcoal smoked turkey
directions: Mix vinegar, water and salt.
Brush turkey well.
Place turkey on hot grill.
Turn and baste every 30 minutes.
Grill for 2 hours.
Remove and wrap in foil.
Place in oven.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and dressing in a small bowl. Press crescent rolls flat in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.
Spread cream cheese mixture over rolls.
Sprinkle with vegetables and cheese.
Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and shortening.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly until smooth and creamy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with milk. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes and Parmesan cheese. Stir in potatoes, then spread in ungreased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch or 3-quart casserole).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
(Eight cups of cubed potatoes can be substituted for the frozen potatoes.)

title: crab bites
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread generously on English muffin halves.
Cut into quarter and freeze on trays.
When frozen, put into plastic bags and store in freezer.
Broil until brown and bubbly before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add all ingredients, except chopped nuts to cream cheese; mix well.
Form into ball.
Chill until ready to serve.
Before serving, roll in chopped nuts.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until well mixed. Serve with sliced apples.

title: mayo's biscuits
directions: Drop onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine
eggs,	sugar and oil;	beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients; mix
well.
Stir in pumpkin.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch floured
and
oiled
cake
pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Drain juice and reserve from tomatoes.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 quart.
Place in kettle with chuck, salt and pepper, celery tops and parsley.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add barley; cook 1 hour longer.
Remove and discard celery tops and parsley.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil. Reduce heat and cook 45 minutes.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in tube pan 3/4 to 1 hour at 375°.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat
eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining
ingredients;
mix
well.
Pour
into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Remove 1 cup pecans.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Make a ball and roll in reserved pecans.
Chill.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir flour, salt and soda.
Fold into creamed mixture, then add oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour.

title: hamburger barley vegetable soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves.

title: "crab" cakes
directions: Whisk milk, egg, Worcestershire and lemon juice in a bowl. Add sealegs, bread crumbs and onion.
Mix well (and let sit about 5 minutes for easier shaping) and shape into 8 patties.
Fry in margarine, in batches, until browned on both sides. Serves 4 for dinner, 8 for luncheon.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add margarine, sugar and flour to corn; heat in heavy pot. Add cream and let heat well; then add the eggs to which the baking powder has been added. Stir well. Pour into buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Chill.
Top with any canned fruit pie filling or fresh strawberries.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Substitute 1/2 cup plain yogurt instead of eggs and margarine and follow directions on box.

title: four layer pie
directions: Put
in
1 cup rhubarb, then pineapple, then apples and then second cup of rhubarb.
Sprinkle sugar over top.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook the spaghetti; set aside. Chop the onion, slice cucumbers and dice tomatoes; mix together. Add spaghetti, Salad Supreme and 1 bottle Italian dressing.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill. Can top with a spoonful of whipped topping and a slice of lemon.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine flour, sugar, cocoa and soda.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended. prepare cream cheese topping.
Pour chocolate batter into paper-lined muffin cups, filling 1/3 full.
Top each with a tablespoon of cream cheese topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until top springs back when lightly touched in center.
Cool on rack.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the vinegar and tomato sauce. Put it through a food chopper.
Add vinegar and tomato sauce. Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Cold pack or pressure.
Pressure for pints for 10 minutes at 5 pounds.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until done and falls off the bone.
Dice other ingredients.
Cut chicken into small pieces. Mix together and add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.

title: barbecue hamburger(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add other ingredients; mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish, cover with soup and sour cream.
Spread stuffing over top.
Pour broth mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn saute
directions: Saute 1 1/2 cups finely chopped onion and 1 cup diced green pepper in 3 tablespoons butter for just a few minutes.
Add 4 1/2 to 5 cups fresh corn cut from the cob and 1/2 cup light cream. Season with 1/2 teaspoon thyme and salt and pepper to taste. Cover and cook until corn is tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked crabmeat
directions: Spray a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Saute onion in margarine. Combine ingredients and fold in egg whites.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 25 minutes at 350° until puffed and light brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Place in baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken and celery and sour cream.
Place mixture over chicken. Add Stove Top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: dilled zucchini
directions: Mix zucchini, celery, onions and salt in large bowl; place layer of ice cubes on top; cover.
Let stand 3 hours; drain well. Combine sugar, dill seed and vinegar in kettle; heat, stirring constantly, to boiling.
Stir in vegetables.
Heat, stirring several times, just to a full rolling boil.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars; place 1 or 2 pieces garlic in each.
Seal, following manufacturer's directions.
Cool jars, label and date.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Cool, peel and slice thin.
Cook chopped bacon and drain on toweling.
Pour off half fat in pan.
Cook onion in remaining fat until transparent.

title: artichoke and spinach bake
directions: Arrange artichokes on bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with thawed, well drained spinach.
Cream together the cream cheese, milk and mayo.
Spread over spinach.
Sprinkle dry cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until hot and cheese starts to lightly brown.

title: baked tuna loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: easy-moist old fashioned apple cake
directions: In a large bowl mix first five ingredients together.
Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add sifted ingredients and fold in apples and raisins or nuts.
Bake at 350° in greased Bundt or 9 x 12-inch cake pan for 45 minutes or until top bounces back when touched lightly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together the pineapple, pie filling and milk.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Blend undiluted soups.
Reserve 1 cup.
Combine remaining soup and rice; pour into shallow baking dish.
Arrange pieces of chicken over rice mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and
pepper. Spread reserved cup of soup over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over.
Cover; bake for 1 3/4 to 2 hours at 350°, or until rice is done and chicken is tender.
Uncover last 1/2 hour.

title: jennifer brittingham's caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy saucepan, combine caramels, condensed milk and 1/2 cup Crisco.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until melted and smooth.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
In a small bowl, beat sugar and 3/4 cup Crisco until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in water, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add alternately with flour mixture, beating well. Spread half of this batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until center is set.
Spoon caramel mixture over cake.
Spread remaining batter evenly over caramel.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 40 minutes.
Loosen from sides of pan while warm. Cool completely.

title: mom's icebox rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into the 1/4 cup of warm water and let dissolve. Pour boiling water over sugar, shortening and salt and let cool. Add yeast, beaten eggs and about 4 cups flour.
Beat thoroughly. Add rest of flour and knead until flour is gone.
Place in covered, greased bowl in icebox overnight.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Place ingredients in a casserole in order listed.
Salt each layer as you place it in casserole.
Top with seasoned hamburger balls.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix jelly and chili sauce in large saucepan over medium heat. Simmer to reduce slightly.
Partially cover if mixture splatters. Meanwhile, mix together first 7 ingredients and form into balls about the size or a ping-pong ball, using the palm of your hand in a rolling motion.
Place on a non-stick cookie sheet and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Put meatballs in sauce and simmer for 30 minutes.
Place on serving platter with a toothpick inserted into each meatball.
Pour some of the sauce over the meatballs.
Serve hot.
They will remain warm for quite some time.

title: almond delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking pan; put in oven at 350° and brown.
Stir 2 or 3 times while browning.
Take half of mixture and place in bottom of pan and cool.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Cover bottom with coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix by directions, pour over coconut and pecans. Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Spoon mixture over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in water.
Blend in flour. Place on floured board and knead for 10 minutes.
Pinch off small strips.
Roll into 12 ropes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush with beaten egg, then sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 6 layer dip
directions: Peel, seed and mash avocados.
Stir in garlic powder, garlic salt, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Spread evenly in 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread on sour cream.
Strain picante sauce (save liquid for other use).
Spoon strained picante sauce over sour cream.
Top with green onions and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sugarplums
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine prunes, raisins and nuts; mix well.
In small, heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and 1/2 cup water.
Over medium heat, stirring constantly, cook until mixture starts to boil.
Boil to 238° on candy thermometer or until a little in cold water forms a soft ball that flattens on removal from water.
Remove from heat; cool 10 minutes.
Pour into small bowl of electric mixer; add vanilla and salt.
Beat at high speed 5 minutes or until mixture is white and creamy.
Stir into fruit mixture; mix well.
Turn into prepared pan; press evenly with spatula.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into 64 squares.
Form each square into an oval; roll in coconut. Store in container with tight fitting lid; place waxed paper between layers.
Makes 64.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Sprinkle with sliced green onions and chopped tomato, if desired. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: adobo(stew)
directions: Cook meat with onions, salt and pepper.
Roast chiles lightly and soak and mesh with onion, garlic and oregano.
Fry in oil. Add mixture to cooked meat.
Add broth, vinegar and bay leaf. Boil until gravy is thick.
Serve in a deep serving dish.
Garnish with wedges of avocados, radishes and onions.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 pan real good. Mix the first 3 ingredients together. Pour in pan (batter will be stiff). Top with the cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar mixed together. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix pudding with milk by hand.
Add Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 13 pan with graham crackers.
Add a layer of filling, another layer of crackers, layer of filling, etc., until all of filling is used.
Top layer should be crackers.
Top with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Mash together yeast cake and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add warm water to yeast mixture and dissolve.
Look for bubbling of yeast after about 5 minutes to be sure your yeast is active or rolls won't rise.
Beat in remaining sugar, salt, eggs and margarine. Add flour.
Cover with
a warm damp towel and then plastic wrap and place in refrigerator overnight.
Three hours before serving, separate dough into two balls and roll out into 15-inch circle. Cut each circle into 12 pie shaped triangles.
Form into horns by rolling from the base of the triangle to the apex.
Place the point down onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise 3 hours. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make jello as directed.
Add cranberries and sauce.
Mix in nuts and crushed pineapple.
Let gel.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Stir all together in a large bowl.
Put in a 14-inch ring pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cocktail balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix and shape into walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot. Freezes well.

title: bread pudding
directions: Stir eggs into milk, then add rest of ingredients.
Stir these ingredients well in the bowl or dish in which it is to be cooked. Sprinkle with cinnamon and mix this in as well or let it stay on top.
Cook at 325° until done for approximately 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit quarters in sugar and cinnamon.
Drop in greased pan or angel food pan.
Stir to a boil, brown sugar and oleo.
Pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Broil the pork chops until no longer pink (this eliminates some fat drippings), approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
When chops are cool, break into pieces and place in casserole pan.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and melted butter; add peanut butter. Mix all together until real smooth texture. Fold in Cool Whip until mixed well. Chill until ready to eat. Take out of freezer about one hour before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all but bread well.
Serve on bread.

title: cocoa fluff frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and beat for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: marinated white bean salad
directions: Cook beans until tender; drain and chill.
Dice onions, celery and bell pepper and add to beans.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: english trifle
directions: Add all above ingredients together and chill for 3 hours.

title: crepes ala crab
directions: If frozen, thaw crabmeat first.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine eggs and milk; brush both sides of chicken pieces with milk mixture.
Place a piece of ham and a piece of cheese in center of each chicken piece.
Brush top of cheese slices with milk mixture.
Fold ends over ham and cheese; roll up, beginning with long side.
Secure with wooden picks.
Dredge chicken in flour; dip in remaining milk mixture and coat well with breadcrumbs.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Heat 1/2-inch oil in a heavy skillet; add chicken and pan-fry over medium heat 20 minutes or until golden brown, turning frequently. Drain well.
Serve with mushroom sauce, if desired.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted oleo together and form crust in greased 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine cream cheese (room temperature) and powdered sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Spread mixture carefully over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and set aside.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Spread over nuts.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes, then carefully spread cherry pie filling over top.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix cider vinegar and sugar.
Microwave for about 3 to 4 minutes.
Put beets in mason jar (or bowl) and pour mixture over beets.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep for weeks.
After beets are gone, put in hard-boiled peeled eggs.
Yields 4 servings. Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and toss.

title: easy coconut-pecan bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour a bundt pan. Mix cake mix, oil, water and eggs for 2 minutes. Add the rest of the ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix soup mix and sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice through entire package of ham.
Spread mixture on ham.
Roll up slice of ham and secure with toothpick.
Repeat process.
Serve with crackers.

title: barbecued polish sausage
directions: Cook onion in hot fat until golden brown.
Combine remaining ingredients except sausage and add to onions.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Slice sausage and add to sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: candied sweet potatoes(this is another good recipe that goes well with ham.)
directions: Peel and cut sweet potatoes or yams in half, and parboil 10 minutes.
Drain and place in buttered baking dish.
Dot the potatoes with butter, and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Add water.
Bake 30 minutes or until tender in a 350° oven.
Check and baste with own juice often.
Serves 6.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon in heavy 1-quart saucepan, drain off fat.
In 1 tablespoon drippings, lightly brown onion, peppers and celery. Add water and salt. Bring to boil.
Stir in rice, tomatoes, sugar and Worcestershire.
Simmer until rice is just tender, stirring occasionally.
Crumble bacon and stir into rice mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and cook over very low heat until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: coconut butter balls
directions: Cream butter. Add 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour all at once and blend well.
Mix in coconut.
Chill 15 minutes, then shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Roll in 10x sugar while still warm.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: squash relish
directions: Soak squash 3 hours in salt water, then drain.
Mix squash in remaining ingredients and boil 30 minutes.
Seal in canning jars.

title: cashew triangles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and egg yolk.
Stir in flour.
Press dough in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), with floured hands.
Beat egg white and water. Brush over dough.
Sprinkle with cashews and press them lightly into dough.
Bake about 25 minutes or until light brown; cool 10 minutes.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Cut each square diagonally in half.
Immediately remove from pan; cool.
Drizzle with chocolate. Let stand about 2 hours or until chocolate is set.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: fried raw oysters
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dredge oysters in crumbs.
Place on a baking sheet and freeze until firm.
Heat 1 inch of oil to 350°.
Fry frozen oysters in oil until golden brown; drain on paper towels.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: bow ties with sausage, tomatoes and cream
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add sausage and pepper flakes.
Cook until sausage is no longer pink, stirring frequently, about 7 minutes.
Add onion and garlic to skillet and cook until onion is tender and sausage is light brown, stirring occasionally, about 7 minutes.
Add tomatoes, cream and salt. Simmer until mixture thickens slightly, about 4 minutes.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.)
Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Drain. Bring sauce to simmer.
Add pasta and cook until pasta is heated through and sauce thickens, stirring occasionally, about 2 minutes.
Divide pasta among plates.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve, passing Parmesan separately.
Serves 4.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, place carrots, onion, stock, bay leaf and thyme. Cover and cook until carrots are tender, about 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Puree.
Season with salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Stir in cream.
May be served hot or cold.

title: susan's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; tear chicken into pieces and place in a greased casserole dish.
Mix topping ingredients together.
Pour mixture over chicken.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix for topping.
Combine remaining mix, butter and egg.
Press into pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put in small bowl and pour dressing over.
Stir well and refrigerate several hours.

title: mom's chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bone.
Mix chicken, mayo, lemon juice, celery soup, broccoli and curry powder.
Place in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, more the better.
Bake additional 5 minutes.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook sausage until done; crumble, drain and combine with the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Cook pineapple to boiling; stir in the perma flo that has been mixed with sugar, water, salt and beaten egg.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cool.
To cooled mixture, add the rest of the ingredients and gently fold in until well mixed.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: tomatoes provencale
directions: Cut tomatoes crosswise into halves.
Place cut side up in shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle cut surfaces with salt.
Blend together butter, corn flake crumbs, parsley and garlic.
Make upright cuts part way into tomato halves.
Spread corn flake crumb mixture over cut surface of tomatoes, pressing mixture gently into upright cuts.
Bake in 400° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water just until tender. Drain.
Drain tomatoes, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
Quarter tomatoes. Stir into noodles along with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Place noodles in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Trim fat from chops.
In skillet, cook trimmings until 2 tablespoons fat accumulates.
Discard trimmings.
Brown the chops in hot fat. Arrange chops over noodles.
Sprinkle with onion.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add
flour
mixture,
milk and vanilla to	creamed
mixture gradually,
beating
after
each addition. Fold in stiffly beaten
egg
whites.
Spoon
batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake until cake tests done. Cool and remove from pans.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Stir in zucchini, cheese and onion; set aside.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Drop batter into 1-inch hot oil (375°) by tablespoons.
Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: fried deer steaks
directions: Mix together eggs and milk.
Dip steaks into eggs and mixture and dredge in flour.
Heat oil and fry steaks over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sue's rice dressing
directions: Melt oleo; saute meat and chopped vegetables until clear. Season meat now.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add 2 cans (soup cans) of water.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda and set aside.
With wooden spoon, mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, nuts and chips.
Then add flour mixture and mix well.
Batter will be thick.
Fold in apples.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.

title: tuna spread
directions: Thoroughly combine first four ingredients.
Turn into serving bowl and sprinkle with paprika.
Chill.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups spread or dip.

title: fabulous fruit salad
directions: Stir the milk and lemon juice together until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir together and chill.

title: banana pudding pie(makes 8 servings)
directions: Prepare pudding as package directs for pie filling, using milk.
Arrange 1 cup banana slices over bottom of crust.
Top with prepared pudding.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack pans with cucumbers, garlic, dill, hot peppers (2 or 3). Add 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1 inch of vinegar.
Fill with tap water; shake.
Put in water bath and boil for 5 minutes.

title: diced apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use sauce on ribs, pork chops, chicken or on anything you grill.

title: pretzel
directions: Add last three ingredients together. Pour over pretzels.

title: carrot and pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar to eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cabbage boil
directions: Place cabbage, mushrooms, carrots and celery in a 4-quart saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until all vegetables are done.
Drain liquid and serve.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread coconut and pecans over bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter over pecans and coconut.
Soften margarine and package of cream cheese in microwave and then mix 1 box confectioners sugar, using electric mixer on low setting.
Mix until creamy.
Spread mixture on top of cake.
Bake for 45 minutes. Allow cake to cool in pan.
Do not remove.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
To the boiling water, add onion and simmer 5 minutes.
Add soup, salt and pepper to cooked onion.
Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole with layer of potatoes.
Cover with thin layer of ground beef.
Top with onion-soup mixture. Continue alternating layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
If needed, add extra water. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Grease baking dish, layer sliced tomatoes and sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
In a saucepan, brown bread crumbs, spices and 3 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle on top of layer tomatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Dot with remaining 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Make stuffing as directed on package.
Add celery and onion. Melt margarine.
Add flour and milk, cooking until thickened. Stir in cheese.
Add creamed corn and broccoli.
Butter a casserole dish.
Layer the stuffing, broccoli and cheese mix. Repeat until all used.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: snack dip
directions: In a saucepan, combine egg, sugar and vinegar.
Cool to thickening (will have appearance of scrambled eggs).
While warm, add cream cheese, onion, pimento or red sweet pepper (optional). Mix well.
Keep well covered and refrigerated.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: fruit salad (pudding)
directions: Mix pudding, milk, orange juice and sour cream or yogurt together.
Drain cherries, oranges, pineapple and peaches.
Put in with pudding mix; add apples and bananas.
Mix all together!

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until smooth.
Chill until firm.
Roll in ball.
Roll in nuts or chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: ground sausage with peas
directions: Brown sausage.
Add garlic and onion.
Add salt, pepper, soy sauce and vinegar.
Stir and heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add green pepper and peas.
Add 1 cup water (more water, if too thick). Simmer until peppers are tender.
Serve over rice.
Just add sage to regular ground pork.

title: sweet lime pickles
directions: Pour lime solution over pickles.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain well; wash well.
Let stand in clear water 3 hours.
Make a solution of vinegar, sugar, celery seed, cloves, spices and salt. Boil and pour over pickles to leave overnight.
Boil in solution 35 minutes.
Seal hot.

title: quesadillas
directions: If using beef, you must cook in a crock-pot all day until the meat falls apart. Remove all fat and pull meat apart into shreds. If using chicken, dice up all meat and then cook in about 2 to 4 tablespoons of oil in a frying pan until chicken is done.

title: sausage and lima bean casserole
directions: In a frypan brown sausage 2 to 3 minutes in water.
Add onion and
green	pepper.
Stir
and cook 3 minutes.
Pour off drippings.	Blend
in flour.
Add olives, tomatoes, lima beans and salt.
Stir.
Put
mixture in a 2 quart greased casserole. Cover and
bake
20 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 20 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: greek meatballs(youvarlakia)
directions: Mix together and form into small meatballs the ground meat, rice, chopped onion, parsley, dried dill and egg.
Roll in flour.

title: crescent roll coffee cake
directions: Press 1 package crescent roll dough over the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, egg yolk, vanilla, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour the mixture over dough. Press the second can of rolls over the filling (gently).
Beat egg white and spread over all.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Roll dough into rectangle shape, 1/4-inch thick.
Cream peanut butter and cream together.
Spread on dough.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Slice 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Bake in moderate oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 12 or more rolls.

title: hot crab and cheese dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, onion, horseradish and garlic powder.
Fold in crabmeat.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2 cup baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve with crackers or chips.

title: green tomato relish
directions: If tomatoes are small, leave them whole.
If they are large, quarter them.
Mix sugar, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add tomatoes, onion, bell pepper and jalapenos.
Simmer 15 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: In skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender. Stir in seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Place dinner rolls in ungreased pie dish, 10 or 11-inch.
Fill and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix together and microwave for 5 minutes. Beat a little and microwave for 5 minutes. Add the pecans and vanilla.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Beat until creamy. Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: coconut cake(happy day cake)
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients for 2 minutes; then add remaining ingredients and beat 1 minute.
Pour into 3 cake pans, greased. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
Let cake cool.

title: parslied new potatoes
directions: Pierce each potato with a fork once.
Combine the potatoes and water in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 4 to
8 minutes, or until fork-tender.
Let stand, covered, until serving time.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: vegetable soup with polish sausage
directions: Cook sausage in 1 tablespoon oil; drain fat. Put tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, bouillon and sugar in pan; bring to boil. Add carrots, celery, zucchini, onions and spices. Add sausage and cook until vegetables are done.

title: crescent caramel rolls(award winning pillsbury bake-off recipe)
directions: Leave crescent rolls rolled and slice each roll into 8 pieces. Melt margarine and brown sugar with water and blend well.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) round cake tins.
Sprinkle with nuts and arrange cut slices in pan (8 in each pan).
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook
and
drain spaghetti.
Rinse in hot water and put into shallow
dishes,
filling them 1/3 full.
Cook onion and garlic in butter for 5 minutes.
Add soups, steak sauce, milk and
1/2 of the cheese.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add chicken, pimento and parsley.
Mix well.
Add pepper to
taste. Pour
over	spaghetti
and sprinkle with remaining cheese and a little paprika.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375°
for
about 30
minutes.
Makes
about 12 cups.
Freezes well.

title: homemade irish cream
directions: Blend well with mixer until creamy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut the eggplant in thick slices, carefully paring each piece. Throw it in salt and water.
Let it remain there several hours. Take from the water; drain and wipe, then butter the slices of eggplant, dip in beaten egg, then in grated cracker and fry a light brown.
Pepper.
Grate more cracker over them and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, vanilla, cocoa, milk and butter in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal, if runny add 1 more cup. Place into balls on wax paper.
Wait to cool to eat.

title: broiled cube steaks
directions: Mix all ingredients (except meat) in a bowl; dip each steak in mix.
Place steaks on broiler pan on rack closest to heat.
Broil 5 minutes; do not turn.
Spoon any juices over steak.
Serve.

title: rolled pot pie
directions: The characteristic flavor of sauerkraut is developed by action of certain types of lactic acid bacteria found on raw cabbage. One type grows best at 60° to 75°; as it grows and ferments, activity raises temperature and becomes slightly acid.
Other types increase acidity.
If temperature is much above 75° at beginning, the first type will not thrive, and flavor of the kraut will be disappointing.
If cabbage is too cold, fermentation may not be complete.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add flour, pineapple and juice, sweet potatoes and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in 3 layers at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Beat shortening, margarine, sugar, egg and almond extract together.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in coconut and corn flakes.

title: plum cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat fruit with syrup.
Blend in cornstarch, dissolved in water.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute. Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Stir Bisquick and sugar together. Stir in milk and oil.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits except banana.
Sift Tang and pudding over fruit mixture.
Stir and refrigerate.
Add bananas right before serving.

title: banana split
directions: Mix the 1 stick oleo with the crushed graham crackers and put in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the 2 sticks softened oleo with the eggs and powdered sugar and beat for 10 minutes.
Put on top of crust.
Add the sliced bananas (layered over top), pineapple on top of that and then Cool Whip on top of the pineapple.
Sprinkle the walnuts and cherries over, then drizzle with the chocolate syrup.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix vinegar and soda in a dish; let stand.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add buttermilk, salt and flour alternately.
Add vanilla, soda and vinegar.
Stir in food coloring and cocoa.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Spread nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix like it says on box.
Spread cake mix over the nuts.
Put cream cheese and butter in microwave until soft, not melted.
Mix cream cheese and butter with powdered sugar.
Pour over the cake mix.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Spoon fudge topping on until it melts, then spread.

title: chile dip
directions: Put the cream cheese in an ovenproof dish, then chile on top to cover cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes or microwave for 10 minutes.

title: spicy cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Add to your taste extra mayo or mustard.
Sprinkle with red pepper for a spicy taste.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Place 2 tablespoons butter in each of 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans. Heat at 425° until hot.
Combine egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Beat at high speed with an electric mixer until thick and lemon colored. Add milk; fold in egg whites.
Dip bread slices into egg mixture, place in hot pans.
Bake for 10 minutes, turn and bake 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: aunt jean's rice dish
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Put cooked rice in baking pan and place broccoli (thawed) over rice.
Spread Cheez Whiz over the top.
Mix in onion-celery mix.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.
Serve with any type of meat.
Serves 4.

title: artichoke and pepper dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in ovenproof dish and heat in 350° oven until hot through.
Serve with taco chips. Good cooled a bit.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Combine mixture. Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Heat cheese and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan over low heat until partially melted, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, green onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes. Spoon into greased 8-inch glass baking dish. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or microwave, covered, on High for 12 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: In a large bowl, with an electric mixer, beat butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Mix in egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Spread dough into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add 1 tsp. vanilla. Roll into shape of a small pecan with a piece of pecan in center. Take two squares of Baker's Chocolate and a square inch of paraffin wax, melt in double boiler and dip candy in it. Quickly place half a piece of pecan on top.

title: favorite hamburger dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Add corn and tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: red beans and couscous
directions: Bring broth, undrained tomatoes, salt, pepper, basil and oregano to a boil in a large saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in couscous.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Stir in kidney beans, oil, onions, parsley and celery.
Serve hot or slightly chilled.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Shred cabbage and carrots and toss with dressing and refrigerate overnight.

title: sugar-free fruit bars(health food)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add oil and apple juice.
Mix well. Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 20 or 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: german steaks
directions: Buy real thin steak.
Lay on cutting board and beat with mallet on both sides until very thin and flexible.
Put salt and pepper, slice of bacon, slices of onion, slice of sweet pickle and a little mustard.
Roll up and put toothpick to hold together. Fry until golden brown on each side.
When golden brown, take out and make gravy.
Then put steaks back in gravy and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: escalloped english peas
directions: Put in baking dish; cover with white sauce.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pitcher or container.
Stir until well blended.
Pour over ice to serve.

title: bacon almond potato balls
directions: Combine potatoes, bacon, butter, green onions and salt.
Chill in fridge for two hours.
Shape into balls.
Roll in flour, egg and almonds.
Deep fry.
Serve immediately.

title: creole string beans
directions: Saute onion and peppers in butter.
Combine beans and tomatoes.
Season and place in buttered baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: pear relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until tender.

title: chicken breast - career wife
directions: Brown the chicken breasts in corn oil in pressure cooker.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, salt and pepper. Cook under pressure about 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Simmer chicken breast until cooked.
Cool and finely dice chicken.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soak gelatin in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Stir well.
Add sugar and pineapple; mix well.
Set in refrigerator until it is a syrup mixture.
Put a layer of cake in pan, then a layer of syrupy mixture and Dream Whip until you have used all cake and mixture.
Then put Dream Whip with coconut on top.
Put in a 10 x 12-inch sheet pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat 5 minutes at medium speed or until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Combine remaining ingredients mixing well.
Sprinkle over top of pie. Bake 10 additional minutes.
Chill before serving.

title: little nothings
directions: Spread preserves on bread.
Roll up like a jelly roll and combine 3/4 cup pancake mix, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.
Add egg and milk.
Pour vegetable oil into deep fryer and allow oil to heat.
Dip each jelly roll in batter and drop into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with sugar.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, cheese and 1/2 c. sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can French fried onions. Pour into 1 quart casserole. Bake covered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all vegetables and cheeses in salad bowl or taco bowl. Top with sour cream and hot sauce.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Chop green onions and mix with coleslaw.
Brown almonds and Ramen noodles lightly in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Mix soy sauce, oil, vinegar and sugar together and cook until sugar melts, about 2 minutes.
Cool.
Mix all together and serve immediately.

title: chicken kraut casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp, drain, then crumble.
Roll chicken in 1/3 cup of flour; brown in small amount of oil.
Using the same pan, saute onions, garlic and thyme.
Blend 2 tablespoons flour with onion mixture.
Gradually add chicken broth; cook until thickened.
Stir in bacon, kraut, sugar and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
