Lay chicken on top; cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to brown.
May be frozen before baking.

title: homemade butter pecan ice cream
directions: Toast nuts in oven about 300° for approximately 10 minutes. Whip cream and refrigerate until needed.
Mix everything together and freeze in an ice cream freezer.
Delicious!!

title: sour cream and chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt in bowl. Add to chocolate mixture alternately with sour cream, beating well after each addition.
Stir in boiling water.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in cold frying pan.
Cook on medium heat 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese and sherry spread
directions: Combine cheese, sour cream and sherry.
Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon or in the bowl of an electric beater until light
and fluffy.
Add more seasonings such as Tabasco sauce, if desired. Chill and serve with buttered toast or crackers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon and lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add water to juice, making 2 cups liquid. Bring to boil and add gelatin.
Add rest of ingredients and congeal.

title: illegally delicious apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice
apples
and
place
in bowl.
Add sugar, tapioca, cinnamon,
nutmeg
and
mix
well.
Add orange juice and lemon juice; mix
and
set aside for about 1/2 hour. Prepare crust for two crust pie.
Fill bottom crust.
Add pats of margarine to top of
filling.
Place
top
crust on pie and make a few slits in it.
Bake
in
350° oven for about 1 hour. For first 45 minutes, cover
top
crust with aluminum foil to prevent burning.
Pie is done
when
top
is golden brown and filling begins to bubble from the crust.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place layer of chicken in pan; cover with
layer
of
vegetables,
layer
of
soup,
layer of chicken, layer
of
vegetables
and	layer
of soup.
Mix corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Spoon evenly over top of last layer.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cornbread is lightly brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Use 1/2 cup flour to dredge nuts, raisins, coconut and dates. Sift all other dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Add pumpkin, beat, then add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Stop mixer and pour in nut mixture and fold in well.
Bake in loaf pans in 325° to 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Don't overcook.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Mix fruit and nuts.
Beat eggs and add all dry ingredients. Mix together and bake in loaf pan, greased and lined with paper, for 1 hour at 275°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all ingredients, creaming shortening and sugar first, then add eggs and dry ingredients last.
Roll into small balls.
Dip into mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen or more.

title: artichoke bottoms with snails & mushrooms(carciofi con funghi e lumache)
directions: Arrange artichoke bottoms in large greased baking dish. Melt butter in medium skillet.
Add shallots and garlic; saute several minutes and then add
snails.
Saute for a few minutes and then remove snails from pan.
Set aside.
Add mushrooms to pan and cook until
mushrooms
are
very
tender.
Add
flour, wine, salt and pepper;
heat
until thickened.
Place 2 tablespoons of filling and 1 snail on each artichoke bottom.
Cover and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove
cover and bake an additional 10
minutes. Garnish with
parsley
sprigs.
Makes
to
6 servings.

title: vegetable soup(meatless)
directions: Slice cabbage, pepper and carrots thin.
Dice the potatoes. Chop onions and saute onions in oil.
Add the water and all of the ingredients.
Bring to a good boil, then simmer for 2 hours. Add a light zaprashka and simmer 15 minutes more.
Season to your taste.

title: chocolate caramels(sooo good!)
directions: Cook the
sugar,
molasses, chocolate, butter, salt and 1/2 of the
cream
to
the thread stage (230°).
Add remaining cream gradually and continue to cook to the hard ball stage at (254°). Remove
from
stove.
Cool.
Beat
well and pour into buttered pans.
Cut into squares when nearly cold.

title: strawberry cheese mold
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O and water; add the berries and pineapple.
Pour in mold and let set.
Mix lemon Jell-O and water; when thickened, add whipped cream and cream cheese.
Pour over strawberry mold.
You may top with whipped cream.

title: snappy apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add apple juice, chill until slightly thickened.
Add apples and celery.
Chill until set. Serves 12.

title: pecan everlight cookies
directions: Beat egg white until stiff peaks form. Add brown sugar. Add nuts. Stir nuts until coated. Place with teaspoon onto nonstick cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 25 minutes. Let cool.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and 1 cup of sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add apple, milk and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients; beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in raisin liquid.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda and salt. Stir in rolled oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: surprise pie
directions: Put egg whites into a bowl;
add baking powder and beat until stiff.
Gradually
add
sugar,
beating
often for each addition. Mix
in
graham
cracker
crumbs, then add nuts and flavoring. Spread in
a
9-inch
glass
pie pan that has been generously greased.
Bake
at
for
minutes or until lightly browned,
cool then spread with whipping cream on top. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Sift in soda, salt and flour a little at a time. Add vanilla and cut up apples and pecans. Cook 1 hour 15 minutes in tube pan.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jamaican jerk chicken(spicy flavor)
directions: Add all ingredients together (except chicken) and blend together until smooth.
Put chicken in a bowl, pour marinade over chicken and marinate for 30 minutes.
Heat broiler.
Put chicken on broiling pan, reserving marinade.
Broil the chicken, basting occasionally, with reserved marinade, until browned, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter.
Using flour, make gravy in pan with chicken broth. Combine all ingredients. Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in casserole dish for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: quick corn tamale
directions: Mix all and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: In large heavy soup kettle, melt butter or margarine; add carrots, celery, onion, green pepper and ham.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Do not brown.
Add broth.
Mix cornstarch, flour and milk together in separate bowl and add to broth and vegetables, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Add paprika, cayenne and mustard.
Add cheese gradually, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Do not allow soup to boil after cheese is added because it will curdle.
Serve very hot. Makes about 2 1/2 quarts soup.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant into very thin slices (1/8-inch). Soak slices in salt water for 30 minutes; drain.
Mix flour and water to a paste consistency.
Dip each slice into flour mixture and cook in hot oil until browned lightly.
Drain and serve hot.

title: kraeer's chipped ham barbecue
directions: Cook all ingredients (except chipped ham) on medium heat until it comes to slow boil.
Cook slowly for about 5 minutes.
Add chipped ham a piece or two at a time and mix into sauce with fork until all mixed.
Cook gently for about 5 minutes.
Serve on soft or hard buns.

title: chili con queso soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook the onion in the butter over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until the onion is soft.
Add the chiles and the tomatoes.
Cook the mixture over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, for 8 to 10 minutes or until the liquid has evaporated.
Stir in cream cheese.
Maintain a moderate to low heat until the cheese is melted.
Stir in the chicken broth, the half and half, the lemon juice, the cayenne and salt to taste. Heat the soup over moderate heat until it is hot, but do not let it boil.

title: scottish oat scones
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add melted oleo, milk and egg. Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in raisins. Shape dough to form a ball; pat out on a lightly floured surface to form an 8-inch circle.
Cut into 8 to 12 wedges.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet in a preheated 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve warm at breakfast or brunch with butter, preserves or honey, as desired.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Sift sugar and flour together. Add eggs and milk. Add melted butter and vanilla. Pour in large pie plate sprayed with nonstick baking spray. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn and set aside in large pan.
(I use an aluminium turkey pan.)

title: chicken in honey sauce
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Brown chicken in oil about 10 minutes.
Stir in carrots, onion, water, vinegar, honey, soy sauce, chicken cubes and reserved pineapple juice.
Cover; simmer 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Stir together cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Stir cornstarch mixture into pan juices.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils, about 2 minutes.
Stir in pea pods and pineapple; cook 1 minute.
Arrange chicken and vegetables on hot rice.
Stove top about 55 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 1 hour.
Add spaghetti, boil 1 hour more.
Add next 9 ingredients and boil 1 hour longer.
Mix oil and flour with a little soup and then add to the soup to thicken. Yields 57 (1-cup) servings.

title: cowboy stew
directions: In large skillet, brown meat and onion.
In large pan, cover potatoes with water and cook.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Serve with corn bread.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water. Mix in pie filling and pineapple. Place in a favorite mold or dish. Chill overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onion with hamburger.
Drain and add other ingredients. Bake for 40 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: graham cracker ice cream dessert
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup peanut butter until well blended using a fork.
Add chocolate chips.
Spread half the graham mixture in a 9 x 13-inch Tupperware container.
Press down. Spread slightly softened ice cream.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Freeze until firm (2 to 4 hours).
Top with the hot fudge mixed with 2 heaping tablespoons peanut butter.
Freeze until firm. Top with the Cool Whip and sprinkles.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix together.
Set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: economy casserole
directions: Cook noodles and add salt.
Brown onions in fat and cool.
Add tomatoes; simmer for 10 minutes.
Arrange 1/3 of noodles in a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with 3 hot dogs.
Add a layer of noodles, 3 more hot dogs and another layer of noodles. Add 2 hot dogs on top.
Pour sauce over noodles and hot dogs. Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Heat soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce to just boiling.
Set aside to cool.
Slice and cook carrots. Cut up onion and pepper.
Add carrots to onion and peppers.
When soup is cool, pour over carrots, onions and peppers.
Mix well. Can keep in refrigerator for at least 2 weeks.

title: lamb and mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Cover with water and add seasonings.
Simmer until meat is cooked.
Add cut mushrooms to meat and continue cooking for a few minutes until mushrooms are done.
Serve with rice.

title: earth bread
directions: Combine zucchini, carrots and bananas.
Add eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in a double boiler. Beat eggs in a bowl, gradually blend in sugar. Add flour and salt, then combine with chocolate mixture. Pour into an ungreased 8 inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool, then freeze. This pie does not require thawing before serving. Freezes beautifully, no hostess should be without one in the freezer at all times. Yield: 6 servings. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: celery pimiento cheese salad
directions: Add vinegar, lemon juice and salt to boiling water.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Put in refrigerator until partially set.
Whip.
Add mayonnaise, milk, onion, celery, cheese and pimiento.
Put in salad mold and in refrigerator until set.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring sugar, water and coffee to a boil; skim off fat.
Let cool.
Pour into 1/2 gallon jug.
Add vodka and vanilla bean. Store in a dark place.
Shake every few days.

title: macaroni and cheese sausage bake
directions: In oven, melt butter in 11x7 baking dish. Add macaroni (uncooked), salt and pepper. Stir. Sprinkle cheese over top of macaroni. Pour milk over macaroni and cheese. Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Then add sausage on the top. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: wild rice, mushrooms, and almonds
directions: Wash and drain wild rice.
Melt butter in large pan.
Add rice, almonds, chives, mushrooms; cook and stir until almonds are golden brown.
Heat oven to 325 degrees.
Pour mixture into ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Heat chicken broth to boiling; stir in rice mixture.
Cover tightly.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender and fluffy.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Add zucchini, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Mix well, then mix in dry ingredients.
Bake in two greased bread pans at 325 degrees for 1 hour or until done.

title: taco casserole
directions: Place corn chips in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Add beans, tomato sauce and taco sauce to hamburger. Spread mixture over chips.
Place tomatoes and lettuce on top and cover with cheese. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: heidi's original carrot cake
directions: Pour batter into 3 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes with margarine and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good for do-it-ahead meals.

title: cookie snack bars
directions: Melt sugar and syrup together.
Add peanut butter and mix well over low heat.
Remove from stove and add nuts, coconut and Special K.
Spread in buttered pan, 8 x 8-inch.
Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler and then spread on other mixture in pan. Do not refrigerate.
Cut in squares after it cools.

title: hearty vegetable beef soup
directions: Heat broth and water.
Add vegetables, meat and seasonings. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add noodles.
Cook until noodles are tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.

title: sad cake
directions: Cream the brown sugar with the eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat until done and drain.
Add salsa sauce and cheese to meat and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with Doritos, tortilla chips or as desired.
Refrigerate any unused dip.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend eggs and corn. Stir into dry ingredients.
Fry in deep skillet in hot oil.
Drain well.
Serve with syrup.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil to dissolve. Mix in pan the remaining ingredients.
Pour juice and fruit (boiling) over dough mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or dough on top is done.
Use a deep dish.
Scrumptious and easy.
Serves 8.

title: rice and beans
directions: Mommy puts milk and a sandwich and coffee in it.
This makes the rice and beans good.
Mix it together.

title: oatmeal raisin bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix together boiling water, raisins, quick oats and lard; let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add syrup, salt and flour. Knead; let rise 1 hour.
Put in bread pans; let rise again.
Bake slowly for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix sour cream, Blue cheese and vinegar well.
Add Good Seasons mix.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Roll out graham crackers (or use already crumbed, 2 cups approximately).
Add to small bowl with cinnamon and powdered sugar.
Melt butter and add to crumb mixture.
Mix well and set aside.

title: super slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, slice onions; set aside.
Brown almonds and sesame seed in small amount of oil.
Crush noodles, add seasoning packages.
(Do not cook.)
Make dressing combining oil, vinegar, sugar and seasoning.
Just before serving, put cabbage and onion in large bowl.
Add noodles, almonds, sesame seed and toss.
Pour dressing on and mix well.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except chocolate bars.
Press into Teflon cookie sheet or well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
While warm, spread with chocolate bars.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: methodist fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat eggs and add to mixture.
Sift baking powder with flour (flour raisins with small amount).
Add flour and milk alternately to butter mixture.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans and pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and spread filling between layers and on top.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Place pineapple in a pot with sugar and flour; cook until thick.
Remove from heat and cool.
Slice bananas and cover the bottom of pie shells.
Pour pecans and coconut in pie shells, leaving some for top of pie.
Pour pineapple mixture over bananas and nuts.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle remainder of nuts and coconut.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients thoroughly.
Add sour cream last. Pour 1/2 batter in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the chocolate chips.
Add remaining batter and the chips. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together. Combine eggs, oil and sugar with apples.
Add dry ingredients and pecans.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, checking after 1 hour. Cook at 350° in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and baking soda mixture.
Add apples and flour.
Turn into 3 bread pans, greased and floured.

title: potato soup
directions: * Or 2 to 6 sliced frankfurters or cooked sausages or 1 cup cubed leftover meat (optional).

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time as
listed.
Drop
by	teaspoon
on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Use a pot with a cover.
Cut veal into small pieces and roll the pieces in flour, pressing in as much as possible.
Put pan on stove with 2 tablespoons of beef drippings or other fat.
When fat is sizzling hot, put veal in and add salt and paprika.
Stir until brown, then add 1 cup of boiling hot water and one small onion, cut up fine.
Cover pan with lid.
Cook slowly until tender, about 45 minutes.
The water will thicken to a nice gravy while cooking.

title: snowballs
directions: In medium saucepan, combine chocolate and milk.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in powdered sugar and nuts.
Chill, then form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Yields about 30 candies.

title: brunch pie
directions: Coat a 9-inch pie plate with margarine.
Mix hash and 1 beaten egg.
Press into plate to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Layer cheese, onion and Veg-All in crust.
Beat together remaining eggs, evaporated milk, flour and mustard.
Pour over mixture in crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until filling is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mock gefilte fish
directions: Slice one large onion and carrot.
Add 2 cups cold water, salt, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon sugar into pot and simmer while preparing fish.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add vegetables and steam for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and cook on low for about 20 minutes. Serve on hamburger buns.
Really delicious and great to serve the family after an evening of baseball or soccer!

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Sift
flour
with
baking
powder,
salt
and cinnamon. Cream the
butter
with
both
sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir half of dry ingredients into sugar mixture, then half of the applesauce.
Repeat.
Fold nuts into batter.
Pour into a well greased
and
floured
x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1
hour
or
until
a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool
in
pan for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Let bread cool completely on wire rack before slicing.

title: grandma irwin's white cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and blend well. Add salt and soda to 2 cups flour and sift together.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately.
Add flavoring (I use 2 teaspoons vanilla or almond flavoring and sometimes add spices such as cinnamon and/or nutmeg).
Add more flour to make a nice rolled cookie.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar; add the dry ingredients.
Add milk; mix well.
Spread on greased jelly roll pan.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle on 1 cup brown sugar.
Top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together.
Keep in refrigerator.
Best made ahead of time.

title: snappy crab dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Refrigerate until time to serve. Quick and good!

title: chorizo soft tacos
directions: Stir often until meat is well browned and potatoes are tender when pierced, about 10 minutes (if potatoes aren't tender, add 1/4 water, cover pan, and cook until tender, 8 to 12 minutes longer). Pour in 2 large eggs, beaten to blend, and stir until eggs are firm, 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove pan from heat and stir in 1 cup shredded Jack cheese.
Serve with warm flour or corn tortillas and shredded lettuce, sour cream, salsa, and chopped onions to add to taste.

title: chocolate-sour cream cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Blend in butter, sour cream, eggs and vanilla on low speed.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool completely and frost.

title: homemade taco mix
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
This is equivalent to one package commercially prepared taco mix.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix together. Chill and serve with potato chips and raw vegetables.

title: pound cake
directions: Let butter, oleo and cream cheese soften at room temperature. Cream cheese, butter and oleo.
Add 1 cup sugar at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Mix at slow speed.
Add extracts.
Grease and flour a tube pan and pour in batter.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: good coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and 1 cup sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternating with sour cream to which the vanilla has been added.
Mix nuts, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Turn 1/2 of dough into greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of nut mixture on this.
Top with remaining batter.
Top with remaining nut mixture.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: no fail fudge
directions: You will need a 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large Dutch oven heat the olive oil and add the onions, garlic and carrots (if using).
Cook slowly for 5 to 10 minutes, being careful not to burn the garlic.
Add the herbs and cook for a minute or two more.
Add the beef and pork and brown well.
Add the tomato sauce, puree and paste.
Stir well.
Rinse the cans with the wine and add to the sauce.
Simmer slowly for 2 or 3 hours.
Stir often! Serves 6 to 8.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt together.
Add syrup and eggs. Beat well.
Add vanilla, melted
butter and chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix lard and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add soda, baking powder and flour.
Then stir in milk; mix well before adding chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: spanish hamburger for 25
directions: If you would like it a little thicker, add more oatmeal.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Fry the chicken breasts in pan until done. Cut into small pieces.
Put in a large nonstick covered skillet. Add soup, paste and sauce mix with 2 cups water. Stir in the oregano, garlic and basil. Bring to a boil and turn down the heat.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: creamy onion cole slaw
directions: Toss onion, cabbage and green pepper together in a large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients separately.
Pour over vegetables. Toss well.
Chill 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: In a large bowl, mix Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, egg, spinach, salt, oregano and pepper.
Spray lasagne pan with Pam.
Put 1/3 of Ragu on bottom of pan, then place noodles on top of sauce.
Use half of cheese mixture for next layer.
Layer sauce, noodles and remainder of cheese mixture.
Top with layer of Ragu and the remaining Mozzarella.
Put water around edge of pan and cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.
Let stand uncovered for 15 minutes before serving.

title: gold butter cake(serves 18)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add to creamed mixture, alternately with eggs, beating well after each addition. Pour into floured-dusted 8-inch tube pan.
Bake for 50 minutes. Cover with Orange Glaze.

title: jalapeno squash relish
directions: Combine processed squash and onions.
Sprinkle salt and set for 1 hour; stir often.
Drain.
In large pot combine sugar, vinegar, processed peppers and spices.
Bring to rolling boil. Add squash and onions and boil for 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal. Put in water bath 1 inch above jars.
Bring to boil and boil 10 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine beans, onion, water, vinegar, garlic powder and jalapeno in saucepan.
Heat over low heat.
Pour hot mixture into dish until it's about 1 to 1 1/2 inches deep.
Cover with Velveeta slices, then sprinkle with Colby and Jack cheese.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.
Heat in oven or microwave until cheese melts.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Stir together flour and eggs.
Then mix together all remaining ingredients with mixer, if preferred.
Put into greased pan and bake in oven at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Mix as given.
Do not use mixer. Mix by hand.
Add raisins last, if desired.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven until done, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: best grilled shrimp ever
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tails on (quick way to devein is to run paring knife down back
of shrimp to splay open, then pull vein out with tip of knife).
Melt butter in small saucepan. Add onion, curry, dill and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes over medium-low heat.
Thread shrimp on kabob skewers (these skewers stick less if sprayed with Pam first).
Brush shrimp with curry butter, using pastry brush.
Grill over hot coals 4 to 5 minutes or until shrimp are fully pink.
Can also be broiled under oven broiler.
Serves 2.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled easily.
Goes well with steamed or fried rice.

title: spritz
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add 1 cup of the flour, the sugar, egg, baking powder, vanilla and if desired, almond extract. Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Force unchilled dough through a cookie press onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are firm but not brown.
Cool cookies on a wire rack.
If desired, dip tops into icing, then sprinkle with chopped nuts or colored sugar. Makes about 84.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the butter, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg until light and fluffy. Add eggs and mix well. Stir in zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well. Alternate adding flour and milk, beginning and ending with flour, 1/3 at a time.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake until tester comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn onto wire racks.
Fill and frost top with cinnamon cream cheese frosting.

title: fruit spread
directions: Mix all together and put in bowl.
Cover with chopped pecans. Serve with cinnamon crisp crackers.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in a large skillet.
Drain fat.
Add soups, enchilada sauce and chilies.
Mix well.
Cook until mixture begins to bubble.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Clean and remove tops of berries.
Mash berries to make 1 cup and put into saucepan with sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Let cool, stir occasionally.
Place remaining berries in pie shell.
Pour cooked mixture over berries in shell.
Let cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Steam broccoli until partially cooked, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to food processor or blender and chop fine.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder; mix thoroughly.
Stir in grated cheese, broccoli and onion.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting in squares. Good to serve in bite size pieces as appetizer.
Freezes well.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix and shape into a round ball.
Refrigerate overnight. Bring back to room temperature before rolling out on floured wax paper.
Bake and cool before adding filling.

title: oreo creme pie
directions: Mix cookies and margarine; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar; spread over cookies.
Mix chocolate pudding according to directions on box.
Spread over top of cookies and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together the sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add carrots.
In another bowl, mix together dry ingredients and combine.
Mix thoroughly for about 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: easy tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add soup, stirring to mix.
Pour into individual molds or a square glass dish.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with cottage cheese, stuffed olives or celery.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Put mix in jar with cover. To make 1 cup hot chocolate, place 1/4 cup mix in cup.
Fill with hot water.
Stir until well mixed.

title: peppers roquefort
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Parboil in boiling water in saucepan, one minute, or in a glass baking dish in microwave 2 minutes.
Drain well.

title: company best pickles
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water.
Allow to stand until next morning.
Drain.
Repeat this procedure on the next 3 mornings.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch pieces. Combine the sugar, spice, salt and vinegar.
Bring to boiling and pour over the cucumbers.
Let stand two days.
On the third day, bring to boiling and seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 7 pints.

title: falls' creek muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine oatmeal, wheat, bran cereal and water. Add oil, eggs, buttermilk and sugar; mix. In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt. Mix well. Combine flour mixture and cereal mixture. Store in refrigerator in plastic container. Use as needed. Add nuts and raisins or chocolate chips when ready to bake. Use paper liners in muffin pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Add nuts, pineapple and sugar. Set Jell-O in icebox until mushy.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Keep in refrigerator until set.

title: cocoa-banana shake
directions: Slice banana into blender; add cocoa, honey and water.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add milk and blend.
Add ice cream; cover and blend until creamy.
Serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Thaw and partially cook green beans, retaining 1/4 cup of liquid. Melt 3 Tbsp. butter into liquid. Add crushed crackers and stir to blend. Top green beans with mixture, melt 1/4 Tbsp. butter and add cheese, simmering until melted. Pour over beans. bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave on high for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool well.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, confectioners sugar and cream cheese; spread over crust. Mix
both puddings and milk until thickened; spread over cream cheese layer. Top
with	rest
of
Cool Whip and chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding eggs one at a time and beating well.
Bake in ungreased angel food pan or Bundt for 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Soften liverwurst and cream cheese. Blend all ingredients together well. Shape into ball using wax paper. Roll in nuts or parsley. Serve with crackers or rye rounds.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Remove flowers from broccoli.
In large soup pot, put broccoli flowers, 4 cups water, chicken broth, broccoli stalks (2 or 3 for flavor only), onion, bay leaves, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat 1 hour, whisking every 15 minutes or so to break up broccoli flowers.
Remove broccoli stalks and throw away. Slowly add half and half or milk to soup.
Stir and cook until milk is hot.
Mix flour with small amount of cold milk and add to hot soup.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Let cool to eating temperature.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, if desired, until melted.

title: easy pleasing meat loaf
directions: Mix water and all ingredients except 1/4 cup of the barbecue sauce. Shape meat mixture into oval loaf in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; top with remaining 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stromboli bread
directions: Raise bread dough according to directions on package.
Cut dough in half after it has risen.
Set 1/2 aside.
Roll dough out on floured bread board or table surface.
Beat 1 egg with 1 teaspoon of water, pepper and oregano.
Spread the egg mixture on top of rolled dough, layer with pepperoni and approximately 6 slices of Provolone and 4 slices of American cheese.
Sprinkle some oregano on top of pepperoni and cheese, then start rolling dough from any side.
Brush some of the egg mixture on top of the bread dough.
The egg mixture will give the bread a golden top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until the top is a golden color. Repeat all of the steps for the 1/2 dough that was set aside.
This recipe makes two batches of Stromboli Bread.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place 1 chicken breast half, boned side up, between 2 pieces of plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Working from center, gently pound chicken with rolling pin or flat side of meat mallet until about 1/4-inch thick.
Repeat with remaining chicken breast halves.
In small bowl, combine cheese and ham.
Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly with salt; spread with mustard.
Place scant 1/4 cup of cheese mixture on center of each breast.

title: french bean and onion salad
directions: Combine liquids and sugar and bring to boil.
Layer beans and onions, alternating.
Pour liquid over.
Let sit overnight.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs.
Pour milk over that.
Then spread evenly the morsels over milk.
Then sprinkle evenly coconut over morsels. Top with nuts.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven until browned. Cool, then cut and serve.

title: liquid sunshine
directions: Mix all ingredients and shake in 1-quart pitcher.
Serves 4.

title: chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together melted butter, hot pepper sauce and vinegar.
Dip chicken in mixture; put in baking pan. Sprinkle with 1 package dry Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Bake until brown, usually takes 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serve with celery sticks and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.

title: quick mostaccioli
directions: Brown beef, oregano and basil.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and let simmer.
Cook noodles by package directions until tender. Pour half of spaghetti sauce in a pan and layer with noodles. Cover with a layer of cheese and remaining spaghetti sauce.
Top with another layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts or at a lower temperature until ready to serve.

title: creamy lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add marshmallows and pineapple. Let get syrupy.
Add cottage cheese, nuts and Dream Whip.
Let jell.
May top with coconut and chopped cherries.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: In the bottom of a greased or sprayed with Pam quiche dish, spread chopped broccoli.
Mix sour cream, cottage cheese, margarine, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour over broccoli. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french pineapple pudding
directions: Put graham cracker crumbs in bottom of pan.
Melt 1 stick butter. Pour over graham crackers and mix it up.
Press out in bottom of pan.

title: german peach pudding
directions: Cream together butter and 2/3 cup sugar.
Beat in egg thoroughly.
Sift together the flour and baking powder, then add in alternately with the milk to the egg and butter mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole or 8-inch baking pan.
Pour over the batter 4 cups chopped peaches that have been sweetened with 1 cup sugar.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 40 minutes or until done.
Serve with or without cream or hard sauce. Can use any kind of fruit instead of peaches (pineapple, cherries, pears, etc.).

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and dice.
Break up bacon into bits.
Chop onions and eggs and combine with potatoes and bacon.
Stir flour and sugar together dry.
Cook the bacon grease, flour and sugar mixture, salt, vinegar, and water until clear and thickened. Stir while hot into potato mixture.

title: coffee punch
directions: Pour coffee over ice cream and beat with mixer until ice cream is partially melted.
Pour into punch cups and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: poke salad
directions: Pick poke salad greens.
Clean greens.
Cook until tender in a saucepan.
Heat oil in a skillet; drain off water and add greens to skillet.
Add salt and eggs when water has cooked away.
Stir until the eggs have cooked.
Happy eating!!

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a casserole dish.

title: large family casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain noodles.
Put in 20-inch baking dish.
Heat cooking oil, onions, green pepper and garlic in a large saucepan.
Cook until brown.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a baking dish and cover.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: mexican salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If you like hot, use hot salsa. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: picnic cake
directions: Boil 1 1/2 cups water.
Pour over dates and soda.
Let cool. Add sugar, shortening, eggs, vanilla, flour, salt and cinnamon. Mix well and pour into 9 x 13 inch greased pan.
Mix brown sugar and chips and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve in pan.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Thaw berries; drain liquid in medium-size pan.
Puree half berries and strain into saucepan (reserve remaining berries). Sprinkle gelatin over berries in saucepan.
Let stand 5 minutes. Heat.
Stir constantly until gelatin dissolves.
Cool. Refrigerate 45 minutes.
Blend graham crumbs and butter in medium-size bowl with fork.
Pat mixture around side, not bottom of pan of an 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: barbecue chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle both sides of roast with meat tenderizer and place in a shallow baking dish.

title: comfort food casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and drain. Add mushrooms, celery, green pepper, onion and garlic. Cook 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Add macaroni and cheese. Serve immediately or place mixture in 2-quart baking dish and refrigerate. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until hot. Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nut bread(4 large loaves)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add flour, baking powder and salt, alternate with milk.
Add Crisco and nuts; mix well.
Let stand about 10 -15 minutes.
Bake at 350 for 45-50 minutes.

title: english muffins
directions: Split and lightly toast English muffins.
Place muffins on cookie sheet.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise and onions or olives and spread on muffins.
Sprinkle tops with bacon.
Brown under broiler.
Quarter muffins and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice hot dish
directions: Brown the ground beef. Combine all ingredients in large casserole.
Bake 3/4 hour.
Stir well. Sprinkle with bread crumbs (optional).
Bake another 3/4 hour.

title: saturday afternoon special
directions: Pick up friends in van.
Drive to mega mall.
Shop 'n charge in either group or pairs.
Don't go alone or you'll have no one to talk you into buying that cute outfit that you'll never wear. Before going home stop for dinner and charge.
Arrive home, tell husband you already ate so he'll have to fend for himself.
Then give him the charge receipts.
Sit down, relax and tell him how tired you are.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: missouri sauerkraut
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain off one-half of grease.
Fry onion.
Add tomatoes and kraut and brown sugar.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: creme de mint cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and add 3 tablespoons creme de mint to the batter and bake as directed.
Cool, then spread on fudge sauce.
Top with Cool Whip, that has 3 tablespoons creme de mint added to it.
Shave chocolate on top.

title: peach cake
directions: Put peaches in a 9 x 13-inch pan (including juice).
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches.
Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Let chill until slightly thickened.
Put cranberries through food chopper. Stir in sugar and pineapple.
Remove seeds and half of rind from orange.
Put remaining rind and orange through chopper with apple. Stir into cranberry mixture and fold into Jell-O.
Pour into mold or container and chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce.
Can be cut into fancy little shapes, if desired.

title: fresh tomato sauce with garden herbs
directions: Heat oil in large deep frying pan over low heat.
Stir in garlic and saute 1 minute (do not brown).
Add tomatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, until mixture boils and sauce begins to thicken (about 15 minutes).
Stir in herbs, salt and pepper and let cook 1 minute.
Toss hot pasta into skillet with sauce and mix thoroughly in the frying pan.
Serve immediately in a warmed serving dish.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the egg and beat well. Stir in milk and soda; the soda should be mixed with the milk before adding.
Add flour, oatmeal and salt and beat until well blended.
Add raisins.
Place in 2 small loaf pans or one large pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mama's doughnuts
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add eggs and milk.
Mix well. Add melted shortening. Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out doughnuts and deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on cake rack and dust with cinnamon or powdered sugar.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix and knead well.
Let chill before rolling and cutting. Roll on dough board sprinkled with flour and sugar.

title: sweet and savory meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, eggs, garlic and shape into balls.
In skillet, brown meatballs in shortening.
Pour off fat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line uncooked pie shell with pecans.
Beat eggs and add sugars and salt.
Add corn syrup and vanilla.
Add melted margarine and pour over pecans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 6 servings.

title: orange-peach marmalade
directions: Remove peel from 1 1/2 oranges.
Grind remaining oranges and peaches.
Measure sugar and mixture cup for cup and boil 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Seal in jars.

title: quick mayonnaise
directions: In a
food processor or blender with the motor on high, blend the egg, lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add the oil in
a slow
stream
and
turn the motor off.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Fold in 3
cups
carrots (finely grated by hand).
Bake in 3 well-greased
and
wax
paper lined pans approximately 30 minutes. Allow cake layers to cool completely.

title: yummy chocolate cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Add to sugar and margarine. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add vanilla and chocolate syrup.
Bake in greased oblong pan 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: 60 minute rolls(makes 30 to 40 rolls)
directions: Place lukewarm milk and yeast in a large bowl, add salt and 2 cups of the flour, beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and melted butter and beat 1 minute.
Add remaining flour and mix.
Let raise 20 minutes.
Shape into rolls, let raise 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sauce may be a little thick and can be thinned by adding a little more water.

title: double cheese macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Alternate layers of macaroni, Cheddar and cottage cheese in greased 2-quart baking dish, beginning with macaroni and ending with cheese.
Melt the 1/4 cup butter in a saucepan; stir in flour to make a smooth mixture.
Blend in milk gradually.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In 2-quart serving bowl (glass, if possible), layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas (thawed and drained), cheese and onion. Spread salad dressing over onions, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with bacon and shredded cheese, if desired.
Makes 8 to
10 servings.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix together. Use straight Kool-Aid for the ice ring if desired. Serves 75.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix together buttermilk and instant pudding; add Cool Whip and 1/2 package cookies.
Mix fruits, then add to pudding mixture. Cover with rest of cookies and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese
until
fluffy. Add and beat powdered sugar. Add peanut butter, then milk.
Then blend in Cool Whip. Pour in graham cracker shell.

title: old-fashioned dumplings
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put 2 cups flour.
Place an indentation in the center and pour in 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Begin working in the other ingredients.
Blend evenly.
Roll on lightly floured surface about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into strips.
Drop into boiling, rich chicken broth.
You will need about 1 gallon of broth.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg and banana.
Beat. Add oatmeal and mix well.
Then add flour, soda and spices. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of bell peppers; clean out inside.
Boil peppers for about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Prepare rice as directed on box. Brown hamburger or chicken and mix in taco seasoning.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Mix together rice and meat.
Stuff inside peppers and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with tops of the peppers and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bechamel sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and simmer a few minutes.
Stir in flour and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until flour begins to golden.
Add hot milk, 2 cups at a time, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for about 40 minutes.
Strain through a fine sieve before using.

title: creole barbecue sauce
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Cook the ingredients for at least 2 hours and then add balance of ingredients.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together. Chill and serve.

title: orange slush
directions: Mix sugar in tea.
Combine juices, vodka, water and tea. Place in container for freezing.

title: sausage soup
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Slice green peppers into strips.
Saute sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic in an 8-quart saucepan.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer on low-medium heat for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: divine divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water
and
salt
in a 2-quart measuring cup or bowl.
Microwave on
High
6 to 8 minutes or until hard ball stage (250°)
is reached.
Beat marshmallow cream in bowl with mixer and slowly
add
hot
syrup
mixture.	Beat
until thickened,	but still
glossy.
Stir
in
vanilla and pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Roll into balls size of small walnut.
Then roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Divide whipped topping among 6 dessert dishes, using about 1/3 cup in each.
With back of a spoon, make a depression in the center and spread topping up sides of glasses.
Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon pudding mixture into dishes and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: egg brunch
directions: Saute bacon.

Remove pan from heat. Add chipped beef, butter and 3/4 of the mushrooms (reserve remaining mushrooms for garnish). Mix well. Sprinkle flour and pepper over bacon and mushroom mixture. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until sauce is thickened and smooth, stirring constantly.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, salt and milk. Scramble in skillet with butter. Alternate 4 layers, two of scrambled eggs and 2 of sauce, ending with sauce in a large casserole dish. Garnish with reserved mushrooms.
Cover casserole and bake in a slow oven at 275° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.
Mix stuffing and butter.
Put half stuffing mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken over mixture.
Combine soups and 2 cans chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Put remaining stuffing on top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy green beans with almonds
directions: Cook and drain green beans.
Saute almonds in the butter until lightly brown.
Add lemon and pepper season salt.
Toss almond mixture with green beans.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Boil for a minute and a half.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Add oatmeal.
Mix all together.
Spoon out on wax paper or aluminum foil.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, onion, pepper, salt, baking powder, Accent and sugar.
When well mixed, add 1 beaten egg, then slowly add milk until the mixture is a thick mush.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; add salt and pepper to taste. Drain fat. Add corn, beans and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Simmer 15 minutes. Serve with crackers or warm flour tortillas. Great for a quick meal! Big hit at the deer camp!

title: sausage muffins
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Reserve drippings.
Add butter to drippings to measure 1/4 cup.
Set sausage and drippings aside.

title: grandma's salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in two tablespoons water until smooth. Watch carefully; will burn.
Stir in cream cheese until melted. Remove from heat.
Add fruit cocktail and salt.
Cover in fridge overnight.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Jiffy mix; add it last.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or a long pan.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: hot dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Heat.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: tomato-cheese rounds
directions: *Cut regular bread, your choice, with cutter to just fit size of tomatoes, about 1 to 1 1/4-inch diameter.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Seal edge.
Brush top with beaten egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: the gift horse famous fried biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water per package directions. Add remaining ingredients and let dough rise. Work into biscuits. Fry in hot shortening until done.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Cook together for 20 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and cinnamon on medium speed for about 1 minute.
Slowly add the eggs and hot milk.
Fold in the bread cubes and raisins and turn into a greased 8 x 8 x 3-inch glass baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes or until the top is light brown and the center is moist but not runny.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: sno-caps(cookies)
directions: Mix and cool several hours.
Drop onto baking sheet by spoonfuls.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, beat well. Combine flour and soda; add to cream mixture alternately with milk. Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese and onion cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cheese and butter in medium bowl until well blended.
Add egg; beat until light.
Add flour, salt and ground red pepper; stir to mix well.
Stir in scallions.

title: mushroom hamburger patties
directions: Mix hamburger, 1/2 cup of soup, onion and egg.
Make patties. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then pour remaining soup with a little water over all and bake 10 more minutes.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in electric mixer bowl; beat until smooth, adding just enough milk for dipping consistency.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble bacon.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings until tender.
Mix bacon, onion, pork and beans, mustard and molasses.
Bake, uncovered, in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown crumbs in oleo.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Add cottage cheese and sour cream to eggs.
Grease casserole and layer the ingredients:
crumbs, noodles and cheese, ending with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours, kneading 3 times during the 24 hours.
Form into 4 rolls (12 x 2-inches).
Place on broiler pan.
Bake at 150° for 8 hours, turning 3 times.
Salami will form its own casing.
Keeps in refrigerator several weeks and may be frozen for 3 months.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: chef's salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, toss together lettuce and romaine or spinach.
Arrange meat or poultry, cheese, hard-cooked eggs, tomatoes, pepper rings and green onions over the greens.
Sprinkle with croutons.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix together soup, cheese and milk. Pour half of mixture into 9 x 12-inch baking dish and set aside. Separate rolls. Place small amounts of chicken at large end and roll up. Place filled rolls into mixture in baking dish. Pour remaining mixture over rolls. Sprinkle some extra cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: candy truffles
directions: Combine chocolate chips, milk, butter and egg yolks.
Cook until chocolate is melted and mixture is thick.
Add rum; chill for 3 hours.
Shape in balls and roll in cocoa mix.
Keep refrigerated in covered container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mary's famous split pea soup
directions: Rinse peas in colander with cold water, picking out shells. Put into a 6-quart pot with water.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes. Turn off heat and let set for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil once more.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: tandori chicken(foreign flavor, healthy)
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Skin chicken, rinse and pat dry.
Place chicken in a leakproof plastic bag (or a bowl) and add marinade to cover chicken pieces.
Marinate for 3 to 4 hours or preferably overnight.
Shake off marinade and grill or bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stir-fried pineapple chicken
directions: Heat oil in preheated wok and stir-fry chicken and green pepper.
When chicken turns white, add rest of ingredients and stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake approximately 1 hour at 350°. Bake with bacon strips on top.

title: vodka sauce
directions: Saute onions, red pepper flakes and parsley in olive oil until onions are see through.
Then put in tomatoes and vodka.
Simmer 15 minutes, then put in heavy cream for another 5 minutes.
Make with ziti.

title: nut roll(makes 4 big ones)
directions: Mix flour, butter, sugar and salt
together.
Add yeast crumbled in warm water and milk.
Beat together with eggs; knead everything well.
Roll and flatten and put 4 pieces in wax paper. Refrigerate 1/2 hour wrapped up.
Roll out.
Fill with crushed nuts, melted butter and warm milk.
Bake at 350°
for about 40 minutes.
Brush top with beaten whole egg before baking.

title: blueberry sweet rolls
directions: Mix 3 cups
flour and yeast in mixing bowl.
Heat milk, 6 tablespoons margarine, sugar and salt in saucepan to 115° to 120°, stirring
constantly.
Add
to yeast mixture.
Add egg; beat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup flour to make stiff dough.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.	Divide into 2 portions.
Let rest for 10 minutes.
Roll each portion into an 8 x 14-inch rectangle.	Brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with
mixture of 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and lemon rind.	Top with
berries. Roll
as
for
jelly roll from long side.
Cut each
roll
into 12 slices.	Arrange in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake
at
350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.	Makes 24 rolls.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix together pineapple and marshmallows and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Also, mix together flour, juice, sugar, vinegar and egg.
Cook until thick and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: nutty choco snacks
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well at medium speed.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Press dough into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and sunflower seeds.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Cook and bone chicken.
Place over broccoli.
Make sauce of chicken soup, mayo and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and butter.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: carol's white wine sauce
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour.
Slowly blend in wine and lemon juice, along with chicken broth.
When thickened and smooth, remove from heat and slowly stir in cream.
Season to taste.
Good served over Chicken Cordon Bleu.

title: oatmeal popovers
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° until golden brown and hollow to a tap.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in water until tender; add soup and cheese and heat until cheese melts (could be shredded).

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Beat
egg
whites until frothy. Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff. Add sugar slowly and beat until glossy and
sugar
is
dissolved.
Add
vanilla and food coloring. Fold in chocolate chips.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Add celery, soup and vegetables.
Add rice and seasonings.
Turn into a greased, 2 1/2-quart cassserole.
Cover.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Place in greased 7 x 11 1/2-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Add taco seasoning.
Simmer while you prepare the rest.
Then place Fritos corn chips on the bottom, then layer meat, cheese, lettuce, onion, tomato, sour cream and black olives.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and salt until blended.
Add milk and egg yolks.
With a wire whisk, beat until smooth.
Add margarine and cook over medium heat until thickens.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Pour mixture into a baked pie crust and top with meringue.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, cocoa, flour, coconut and nuts.
(Batter will be thick.)
Grease and flour a 10 x 14-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven, add a jar of whipped marshmallows over cake and spread.
When cooled, frost with chocolate frosting.

title: favorite sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour several times; add soda and resift once.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add flavoring and pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken florentine
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, brown chicken. Spoon off fat and add mushrooms and spinach.
Cook until done. Prepare fettucine and alfredo sauce according to directions.
Mix all ingredients together and serve with Italian bread and salad.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix 1 egg, cake mix and margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix well:
powdered sugar, 3 eggs, cream cheese, and flavoring.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes until golden brown.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: rice primavera
directions: In large saucepan, cook mushrooms, onions and celery in margarine.
Add water, rice, bouillon and Italian seasoning. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add cheese, pepper, peas and carrots.
Cook 5 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Prepare sauce by sauteing onions in oil until tender.
Stir in next 9 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Boil shrimp in water for 5 minutes or until pink.
Add cooked shrimp when ready to eat.
(Even better when sauce is made the day before and reheated.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: autumn soup
directions: Note: Other vegetables may be added.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Saute meat; add taco seasoning mix and 1 cup water.
Cook until thickened.
Combine salsa, corn, chilies, tomato sauce and olives.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam; add layer of tortillas on bottom, layer of meat mixture, 1/2 of salsa, corn, chili, tomato sauce, olive mixture and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn hot in slow oven. Cook sugar, water, salt and corn syrup to very hard ball stage. Add vinegar and some vanilla. Cook to light crack stage.
Slowly pour over popcorn. Stir well to coat every kernel, then press into balls. Use fat on hands if necessary.
Makes 20 popcorn balls.

title: canadian crepes
directions: Mix dry ingredients (flour and sugar); add milk and add eggs and then butter.
Whip by hand.
Let sit for 15 minutes.
In pan with little butter on medium heat, cook and flip quickly.

title: quick graham cracker squares
directions: Mix and
bake
in greased 9 x 13-inch pan 30 minutes at 350°. Cut
in
squares.
Fun
and easy enough for children to make.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method. Stir in salt, flour and baking powder.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: peach cheesecake
directions: Boil water, cornstarch and sugar until thick.
Add jello powder; stir and chill.
Add peaches to mixture.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, press crust (crushed graham crackers and margarine) to bottom. Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Pour peach mixture over creamed mixture.
Chill until set.

title: banana spice pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch (26 cm) Bundt or tube pan.
Whip egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and sugar gradually, beating until peaks form.
In another bowl, cream together the butter and remaining sugar.
Beat in yolks gradually.
Add orange juice. Combine flour, baking powder remaining salt and cardamom.
Add to butter mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Blend in egg whites gently.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Cook green beans in boiling water until crisp tender.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Cut into 2-inch lengths.
Place in large salad bowl.
Add cucumber, tomato, ham, turkey, cheese and olives.
Whisk together oil, vinegar, parsley, mustard, sugar, cayenne, paprika and garlic.
Pour over salad and toss.
Refrigerate a couple of hours and serve.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Knead for 10 minutes. Place in a greased bowl with a lid. Store in the refrigerator until needed. Make into rolls. Cover and allow to rise for 1 hour at room temperature. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: Bring water to boil; add nuts and boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain in colander and rinse under hot water.
Drain.
Mix with sugar and let stand 5 minutes until sugar dissolves.
Heat 1-inch of oil in skillet to 350°.
Add half the nuts and fry 5 minutes or until golden.
Spread on brown paper to drain.
Repeat with last half of nuts.
Salt, if desired.
Keeps in airtight container for 2 months.

title: nannie's goulash
directions: Cut sausage in pieces.
Brown in margarine.
Remove sausage. Brown onions, peppers and garlic.
Add this to remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Cook shell macaroni by directions.
Drain; serve sauce over macaroni.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Saute onion.
Add chicken, celery, carrots and onion to chicken broth.
Cook a few minutes.
Then add potatoes and salt and cook until done.
Add creamed corn, milk, pepper and parsley. Heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Boil water for egg noodles.
Cook noodles while preparing hamburger.
Crumble hamburger and brown in pan.
Add flour, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain grease.
Add cream of chicken soup; stir and let simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream; stir and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: musliex bars
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and boil to firm ball stage.
Toast the oats and wheat germ.
Mix with the sesame, sunflower seeds and apricots.
Add hot mixture.
Pat into pan. Cut when firm.

title: baked whipped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hoot 'n holler hush puppies
directions: Preheat deep fryer of oil to 350° to 375°. Mix cornmeal, flour, baking soda and salt. Add egg, milk and onion. Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat.
Fry until golden turning once. Drain and serve with favorite dipping sauce.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown chops in frying pan with garlic.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Lightly mix together 1/4 cup butter and soft bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons onion and 1/4 cup water.
Spoon this mixture on top of chops.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/3 cup of water.
Pour over chops.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta mexicana
directions: Brown onions in butter in saucepan.
Add chilies, tomatoes and chili to pan.
Cook over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Serve sauce over pasta. Serves 4.

title: black olive cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Form into ball.
Chill. Roll into chopped pecans or walnuts before serving.

title: cabbage and ground beef
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage and drain.
Brown beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake covered at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tropical sauce for ham
directions: Simmer raisins in water 10 minutes.
Stir in orange juice concentrate, pineapple, fruit cocktail with syrup, cherries, pecans, cinnamon and cloves.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Blend together cornstarch and lemon juice.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Cook and stir until sauce is thickened and smooth.
Makes 3 cups.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown steak and onion in butter; stir in soup, water, sour cream and paprika.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry fantasy salad
directions: Blend jello, sugar and water.
Stir in fruit.
Chill until jelly-like.
Whip the sour cream and fold into mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: crab on english muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Spread on English muffin halves.
Slice each half into quarters.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Once frozen, place in airtight container or Ziploc bag.
Keep frozen until ready to use.
Put under broiler until bubbly; if frozen, cook 8 to 12 minutes, unfrozen, cook 2 to 5 minutes.
Great to make ahead for company during the holidays.

title: vegetable spaghetti
directions: Melt butter or heat oil with garlic.
Simmer for 1 minute.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Toss to coat with oil.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Uncover and simmer until tender.
Add tomato sauce and stir well.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve over hot pasta.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix up like regular cornbread.
Add bacon, corn and pepper. Pour into the skillet and put cheese on top. Then punch cheese down into mixture.
Don't let cheese get on bottom or side of skillet.
It will stick to your skillet.
Cook at 425° to 450° until brown.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread beans on a large platter, leaving 1 inch around edge for nachos.
Mix avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Layer on top of beans.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Layer on avocado mix.
Layer green onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese in that order.
Place nachos on edge of platter.
Dip chips into dip.

title: strawberry bread(quick and easy)
directions: Preparation: 10 minutes.
Cooking Time: 60 to 70 minutes. Temperature: 350°.

title: lemon cinnamon gelatin
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Dissolve candies in 1 cup hot water.
Add to gelatin with ice water, lemon juice and applesauce, mix thoroughly.
Cool until slightly thickened and stir in nuts.
Cream cheese with mayonnaise and swirl mixture through gelatin.
Chill in mold until firm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Pressure cook the chicken.
Place frozen broccoli in large baking dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over chicken.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels in a double boiler.
When melted, put in a bowl. Add peanut butter and shoestring potatoes; mix.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, salt, black pepper and oil.
Add tomatoes and spice.
Add sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 or 3 hours.

title: italian cheese bread(makes 2 round loaves)
directions: In small saucepan, heat the milk, hot enough not to burn your little finger when you test it.
Add the sugar; stir.
Dissolve the yeast in the milk.
Make sure yeast is dissolved; set aside. In large bowl, beat the eggs.
Add melted butter, cheese and salt; beat well again.
Add the milk mixture; stir well.
Start adding the flour, 1 cup at a time, until it starts to form into a ball. Turn out onto floured board.
Add enough flour to make a nice soft dough.
Knead for about 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half to form 2 round loaves.
Let rise, covered, in warm place until double in size.

title: southwestern bread dip
directions: Slice the top of the round bread and reserve this for the "lid".
Carefully scoop out the inside of the bread to leave just the sides and bottom like a bowl.
Keep the bread you scoop out for bread cubes later.
Mix all the other ingredients well and then place inside the bread bowl.
Put the top piece of bread on and then cover the entire loaf with foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and serve while hot.
Cut up the bread from inside the loaf into cubes or sticks and place on a cookie sheet to toast.
You can toast these during the last 10 minutes of baking time or after removing the dip from the oven.
Place these on a tray around your dip and serve immediately.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine oil and sugar. Mix well. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg. Sift dry ingredients together. Add half of dry ingredients to oil and sugar. Beat well and add remaining flour; beat well. Add apples and nuts last. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato wedges
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges.
Combine all ingredients, except parsley flakes.
Add potato wedges, tossing to coat.
Microwave at High for 8 minutes or until tender.
If using conventional oven, bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine pineapple and cream cheese.
Add strawberries, marshmallows and Cool Whip. Set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water. Add strawberry mixture.
Put in Pyrex dish.
Cool overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple cake and frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool cake before frosting.

title: moist apple swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan or a 10-inch tube pan.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour 1/2 of batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan for 25 minutes; turn onto serving plate.
Cool completely.
If desired, dust with
powdered sugar.
Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: special tuna patties
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Combine stuffing mix with its seasoning packet; add 1/4 cup hot water.
Mix in tuna.
Mix 1/2 cup milk with 1/2 of soup; add to mixture.
Blend in well beaten eggs. Form mixture into patties and brown lightly in butter.
Place in flat baking dish.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 can soup. Pour over patties.
Bake about 20 minutes at 325°.

title: atlanta gas light mini pizzas
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet on temperature controlled gas burner set at 250° to 275°.
Add tomato paste, onion, seasoning and water.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Separate each biscuit into 2 layers and place on baking sheet.
Lightly flour the bottom of a custard cup and make a shallow center in each biscuit for filling.
Brush biscuits lightly with melted margarine.
Bake in 400° gas oven for 10 minutes.
Fill centers with meat mixture.
Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Broil 3 to 4-inches from gas flame for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in oil and margarine until tender.
Add cooked rice and shrimp.
Cook until done.
If on the dry side, add margarine as needed.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix hash brown potatoes, soup, onion, sour cream and cheese.
Top with pats of oleo, bread crumbs and bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Great!

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1 1/2 cups lukewarm water.
Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Stir in yeast mixture until flour is moistened.
Chill, tightly covered, overnight.
Knead on floured surface for 5 minutes; shape as desired.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush with butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into two (9-inch) pie pans.
Bake at 350° until brown on top, about 35 minutes.
