title: raisin-nut bread with dates
directions: Boil water and raisins together for 1 minute.
Cool.
Mix and cream together sugar, shortening, egg, salt and vanilla.
Add raisins and water to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill 3 or 4 cans (greased) half full.
Use 17 ounces can of peas or corn.
Place on baking sheet so they don't touch.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender, about 10 minutes; drain and mash.
Add onions, carrots, soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Butter 2-quart shallow baking casserole (9 x 12-inch).
Sprinkle half the stuffing on bottom of casserole. Cover with squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Chill jello until it begins to thicken, then add all the rest of ingredients and chill.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on side panel.
While noodles are cooking, beat egg yolk lightly with fork and add to cream.
Melt butter.
Place drained, hot noodles in warm serving bowl or platter.
Pour over the noodles, egg and cream mixture, melted butter and about half of the grated cheese.
Toss noodles with fork and spoon until well blended, adding balance of cheese a little at a time while tossing.
Top with additional grated cheese if desired and serve immediately.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: harvard beets(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Drain beets and reserve juice.
Make a white sauce by melting butter, then stirring in flour to make a paste.
Slowly drizzle beet juice into flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Taste and make any necessary adjustments.
Add beets.
Let sit for a while, then heat beets.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add nuts last.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 25 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Saute hamburger and drain.
Add chopped onion and potato and tomatoes and rest of the ingredients.
Also you can add any other veggies if you would like.
Season to taste.
This is very good with corn bread.

title: icing
directions: Combine flour and milk.
Cook until thick.
Cool in refrigerator.
Gradually beat the sugar into the Crisco.
Blend in the flour and milk mixture.
Add the vanilla and salt; beat until fluffy, about 15 minutes.

title: rabbit pie
directions: Cook
and drain the rabbit.
Debone the rabbit.
Retain the liquid
of
vegetables
and
rabbit for gravy.
Spread the vegetables evenly in the deep pie crust, then place the rabbit on top.
Cover
with the top crust and seam the dough together along the
edges to completely encase the meat and vegetables. Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes or until crust turns golden brown.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice custard
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Let milk cool slightly, then pour egg mixture into milk.
Add rice and flavoring.
Pour into well buttered casserole (2-quart).
Set it in a pan of hot water and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle marshmallows over top and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat for 4 minutes, scraping bowl often.
Pour batter in a greased and floured Bundt pan; bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes; turn onto a cooling rack.
Frost with a thin white icing.
Grated orange rind could be added to the icing for added flavor.
Can also be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks and lemon juice. Pour into pie shell, let chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute one medium onion and raw cabbage in pan with butter. Cook 15 minutes.
Add one ripe tomato, cook 5 minutes and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: In small bowl, mix cream cheese with margarine.
Add bacon bits and chives and blend well.
Form in a ball.
Mix cheese (Old English works well) and liquid smoke.
Form around the cheese ball.
Chill overnight.

title: sausage and grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in a large saucepan with the water and salt following package directions.
Fold in cheese and mix well.
Add eggs, milk, thyme and sausage, stirring until all ingredients are well combined.
Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour in greased pan in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: quick spinach soup
directions: Combine cooked spinach and condensed cream of chicken soup. If the spinach has already been creamed, use instead the chicken broth.
You may thin the soup with spinach water, stock or milk. Season to taste.
Heat and serve.

title: lo-fat blonde brownies
directions: You will need waxed paper cut to fit bottom of two 8-inch square pans.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse beans; place in large kettle.
Cover with water; add salt and soak overnight.
Drain; add 2 quarts water and ham. Simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 or 3 hours.
Add onion, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Simmer for 45 minutes; add salt and pepper.

title: velvety custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar and vanilla slowly.
Stir in hot milk.
Pour at once into pie shell.
Top with dash of nutmeg. Bake in preheated 475° oven for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted halfway down center comes out clean.
Delicious served warm.

title: apple-carrot salad
directions: Peel and grate carrots.
Cut apples into small chunks. Combine last three ingredients and add to apples, carrots, raisins and nuts.
Mix and serve.

title: kielbasi
directions: Cut up the kielbasi into pieces.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Add the mixture to the kielbasi and simmer 1/2 hour. Thicken if desired.
Serve.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Add 3 cups water to jello and tapioca and bring to boil, stirring often.
Cook until thick, then add oranges, marshmallows and Dream Whip.
Refrigerate until firm in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Cut cheese in small pieces.
Place in double boiler and melt. Add flour, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Cook 10 minutes. Add beaten egg.
Cook about 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat. Add chopped pimentos.
Cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and Cool Whip. Add enough milk to give the desired sauce thickness. Toss with remaining ingredients. Can be served right away, but it is best if chilled overnight in covered dish.

title: mom's muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, mix dry ingredients and make well.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients and pour into well.
Mix to moisten.
Do not overmix.
Pour into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add well drained fruit if desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Pour over remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill overnight.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Cut each pepper in half lengthwise; remove veins and seeds. Drain on paper towels.
Mash the cream cheese with sour cream; stir in garlic salt and onion.
Mix well.
Stuff each pepper half with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Chill before serving.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Flake, remove bones and skins from salmon.
Blend in egg.
Stir in liquid, cornflakes or crumbs, lemon, onions and salt and pepper. Spoon into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popped corn and stir evenly.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Place in oven 2 hours at 200°.
Remove and break in pieces.
Store in tight container.

title: pudding pop snacks
directions: Prepare pudding with milk.
Pour into 6 (5 ounce) paper cups. Insert wooden stick or plastic spoon into each for handle.
Press a square of aluminum foil down onto pudding to cover.
Freeze until firm, at least 5 hours.
Press firmly on bottom of cup to release pop.
Serves 6.

title: green bean salad(the delicious boston style!)
directions: Place green beans and pimientos in a mixing bowl.
Put the onions and celery through the fine grater of a salad shooter or coarse chop of a food processor. Add to the beans.
Now is a good time to add a little salt and pepper.
If you have used the salted canned beans, use your judgment on the salt. Gently toss in mayonnaise until beans are lightly coated and all ingredients are mixed together.
Place in serving bowl, garnish the edges with tomato wedges and sprigs of parsley, then shake on paprika and parsley flakes.

title: mary's one pot meal on the grill
directions: Wash roast.
Salt, pepper and sprinkle with garlic.
Cut potatoes (choice of shape).
Wrap all in foil and put on grill for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Turn over every 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, 1 1/2 cups water and salt in pan.
Heat to boil. Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup water to make a smooth paste.
Add to boiling mixture, gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Combine egg yolks and lemon juice. Stir into thickened mixture.
Return to heat and cook until bubbles again.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon peel.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: campfire venison stew
directions: Brown meat in bacon grease or bacon.
Add onions, celery, seasoned salt and pepper.
Cover with desired amount of water and cook 1 hour.
Add bay leaves.
Check to see when meat is tender. Add carrots and cook a bit before adding potatoes.
Then add potatoes and cook until tender.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch to make gravy.
Best when cooked in cast-iron Dutch oven!

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugar, egg, vanilla and lemon rind.
Gradually add flour mixture (flour, salt and baking powder).
Mix well.
Add walnuts. Roll into a log.
Wrap in foil; refrigerate 24 hours.
Slice as thin as possible.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: wellesley fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate, 1/2 cup of the sugar and the water in large microwavable bowl on High 1 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring once.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Put 1/2 of mixture in a meat loaf pan.
Put a hole in the middle and put the chopped onion, bell pepper, garlic and tasso, plus 1 link of sausage in the hole.
Put the remainder of the meat on top.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°, then take out and drain and turn over.
Cook approximately 30 more minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes and mash.
Add salt and pepper. Stir in butter and milk.
Bring to a slow boil, stirring frequently, boiling for 5 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; beat well.
Set aside.
Place bread in a single layer in a shallow dish.
Pour egg mixture over bread; turn slices to coat evenly.

Cover and refrigerate 8 hours. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet; arrange 3 slices bread in skillet and cook 3 minutes on each side or until browned. Repeat procedure with remaining butter and bread slices. Sprinkle toast with powdered sugar.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cream butter.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Work in flour, then add nuts.
Shape into crescent shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil milk and sugar (and cream of tartar if used) for 10 minutes.
Add peanut butter; stir until thick and creamy.
Pour onto greased platter; let harden.
Cut into bite size squares and serve.

title: make ahead seafood stew
directions: Cook onion and celery in olive oil until soft, but not brown. Add saffron and cook 1 minute while stirring.
Add tomatoes, along with reserved liquid from the tomatoes and clam juice.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate overnight. Reheat 1/2 hour before serving and add wine.
Fifteen minutes before serving, add snapper or grouper and assortment of mussels, shrimp, scallops or clams according to your taste.
Serve in shallow bowls with French bread and a green salad on the side.
If you like wine, muscadet is best with this stew.

title: ambrosia
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, slice banana.
Drain mandarin orange sections and pineapple chunks.
In medium bowl, mix banana, mandarin oranges, pineapple and fruit cocktail with its juice. Spoon fruit into 3 dessert bowls; sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 3 servings.

title: honey carrots
directions: Saute onions in butter over low heat until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and stir. Cover and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Pour over ingredients and mix.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together the margarine and shortening.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Gradually add flour mixture to margarine mixture, beating until well mixed. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Remove cookies to cooling rack to cool. Yields 54 cookies.

title: peanut butter supremes
directions: Blend shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar and brown sugar, blending well.
Beat in eggs until fluffy.

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour and salt; set aside.
Melt butter; add sugars, eggs and water.
Mix. Add to flour and mix.
Add chocolate chips and oatmeal.
Add vanilla last.
Bake at 350° on greased round cake pans 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook, bone and finely chop chicken.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth.
Drain. Combine all ingredients and put in large casserole.
Heat about 10 minutes.

title: hildegarde salad
directions: Boil the pineapple juice; beat the eggs lightly and add sugar and flour mixed.
Add butter.
Cook until thick.
When cooled, add to fruits.
Just before serving, stir in the whipped cream.

title: lasagna
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook onions, garlic and oregano. Add soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring now and then.

title: diabetic macaroon cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Combine coconut, cake flour and baking powder.
Beat whites until light.
Add cream of tartar and sweetener, beating until peaks form.
Fold whites into coconut mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoons into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Each cookie contains 3 calories.

title: date drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk; sift dry ingredients together twice.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Add dates; drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Line
dish
with
deboned
chicken.
Pour
broth
over chicken.
Spread
cream of chicken soup over the chicken.
Cut boiled eggs and put on top of chicken mixture.
Mix flour with milk, then pour over the mixture.
Dot butter on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Do not stir.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles in salted water as usual and drain. Mix with beaten eggs, sugar, salt and cinnamon. Add oleo, raisins, nuts and apple, which has been peeled and finely sliced. Mix and place in greased baking pan or dish. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until apple is done and top is browned to liking. Serve hot.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Season pork with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cook.
Saute onion and celery.
Moisten bread with water. Add eggs.
Mix all together. Stuff bird.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving the noodles and almonds for the top.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Follow directions to make brownies.
Place in baking pan. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Cut up cookie dough and place on top of brownie mix and nuts.
Bake per instructions on brownie mix box. Cool and frost.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Thaw fish.
Divide into 3 portions.
Dip fish into beaten egg, then into bread crumbs.
Place fish into shallow greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drizzle mixture of butter and lemon juice over fish.
Then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 500° oven until golden brown and fish flakes easily with fork, 6 to 8 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine butter and crumbs and sprinkle over pineapple.
Bake uncovered 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: blueberry jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups water (1 hot and 1 cold) and juice from fruit.
Add fruit and nuts; let congeal.
Whip cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Pour over salad and refrigerate.

title: beef stroganoff (aunt betty's)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add onion until hot.
Add juice, salt, celery salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over low heat approximately 20 minutes.
Add green peppers, sour cream and mushrooms.
Stir until mixture is hot.
Serve with noodles.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cheddar cheese and paprika in a baking dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature a few minutes before serving.
Can be assembled ahead of time.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and butter.
Boil for 3 minutes. Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into pan.
Makes 5 servings.

title: speedy baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes, until beans bubble. Serves 4.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beat well.
Add vanilla and sweet milk.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add flour, mix well.
Let flour be the last to add, beat until creamed and smooth.
Bake in tube pan in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours, then turn oven down to 300° after first hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Add lemon juice to the sugar.
Beat the yolks of the eggs until light.
Add cornstarch which has been dissolved in a little cold water.
Mix well with lemon and sugar.
Start cooking, then add boiling water.
Cook until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts in 4 cups water in crock-pot until done. Bone chicken and set aside.
Strain broth and pour into large pot. Add the 2 cans of soup, chopped onion, sage and salt.
Stir well and simmer until onion is soft.
Cook noodles; drain and add to soup.
Cut chicken in small pieces and add to soup.
Stir carefully and keep hot until served.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Grease Pyrex dish and set aside.
In large heavy saucepan slowly warm canned milk and sugar until sugar is completely dissolved.
Add Eagle Brand milk and oleo.
Bring to boil and then let boil for 9 minutes, stirring continuously.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir until completely melted.
Put into greased Pyrex dish; let cool, then cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: eggs ala king
directions: Cook celery, pepper and onion in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Stir in cream of celery soup, milk and cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.

title: refrigerated cucumber pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, salt and sugar; blend until sugar is dissolved. Add other ingredients.
Put in Tupperware and refrigerate.
Keeps for weeks.

title: stir bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of water; set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Stir with a spoon.
Add cup with yeast and other cup of water and stir until mixed (do not overdo it).
Cover and let stand in a warm place until dough doubles in size (approximately 1 hour).
Stir again and divide dough into 2 units and place into ovenproof bowls.
Place in warm place and let double again.
Put into a preheated oven at 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: gourmet potato casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Saute onion in margarine.
Pour onion mixture in deep bowl.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well with wooden spoon.
Spread into pan. Crumble 2 cups potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Roll out and cut in squares.
Spread melted butter over each square and fold into triangles.
Spoon into baking pan and cover with a wet cloth for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Add potato chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Form into balls size of a walnut. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Leave on hot cookie sheet for a few minutes.
Makes a lot.

title: oreo cookie ice cream cake
directions: Mix and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze 1/2 hour.
Spread 1/2 gallon softened vanilla ice cream on top of crust.
Freeze 1/2 hour.

title: spiced hot cider
directions: Heat in a large pot and simmer until candy is dissolved.

title: penne with ricottaby - felicia r. mcclinton
directions: Get a saucepan and boil water mixed with salt.
Cook the Penne and make sure to follow the directions provided on the packaging.
After cooking, drain but make sure to leave approximately 2 to 3 tablespoons of water.
Then add cottage cheese and season the dish with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle parmesan cheese on top before serving.

title: mommy muffins
directions: Toast English muffins; heat scrambled eggs.
Brown meat; place slice of meat on toasted English muffin.
Top with 2 tablespoons of scrambled egg, then slice of cheese.
Top with 1 teaspoon mayonnaise and muffin.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and oil until crumbly.
Add vinegar and water, one tablespoon at a time, until mixture is slightly sticky.
(I usually use about 3 tablespoons of water.)

title: super philly beef sandwiches
directions: Heat margarine in skillet.
Saute mushrooms, onion and bell pepper until tender.
Heat oven to broil.
Place bottom halves of rolls on a cookie sheet.
Layer vegetable mixture, beef and cheese on bottom halves.
Place tops of rolls on cookie sheet.
Broil until cheese is melted, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: lime cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Mold and chill.
Serves 8.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and flour.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Cook in preheated oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: almond danish
directions: Cut 1/2 cup butter into flour.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of water.
Mix with fork until blended.
Round into ball and divide in half.
Spread each half onto ungreased baking sheet, making 2 strips 12 x 3-inch about 3 inches apart.

title: sour cream cheese cake
directions: Mix well; spread on bottom and sides of well-greased spring-form cake pan.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Dice onion.
Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain.
In an 8-quart soup pot, add tomato soup, water, tomatoes and Veg-All. Heat thoroughly.
Add ground beef and onion.
Cook until vegetables are done.

title: organic garden vegetable soup
directions: Place bones in a large pot. Cut meat in cubes and place in pot with bones. Add water and spices; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes and all vegetables which have been washed, peeled and diced. Add rest of seasoning. Cook another 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove bones before serving.
Yields 25 servings.

title: barbecued meat balls(makes 72 meat balls)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make into tiny meat balls.
Brown in shortening.

title: corn, cheese and chili pie
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray two 9-inch pie plates with Pam.
Mix all ingredients in the large bowl with the eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pie plates.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes before cutting.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Chop bell pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and serve hot or cold.

title: cookies made from cake mix
directions: Choose a cake mix and add eggs and vegetable oil.
Mix well. You can add other ingredients like nuts, raisins or chocolate chips, if you like.

title: special carrots
directions: Mix all up, then eat.

title: pineapple cheese cake(yield:  9 servings)
directions: Combine onion and ground beef.
Place in nonstick skillet and brown, draining off fat as it accumulates.
Add tomato paste, water, spices, herbs and tomatoes.
Simmer 1 or more hours, adding more water if needed.
Serve 1/2
cup sauce over 1/2 cup cooked spaghetti.

title: vegetable garden dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.
One tablespoon contains 40 calories.

title: spaghetti
directions: Dice and peel garlic.
Chop onion.
Brown meat with garlic and onion, then add tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Mix well, then turn heat down.
Add Italian seasoning and let simmer 1 hour.
Cover skillet to prevent loss of water.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cream the 2 sticks butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients and nuts.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham and cauliflower casserole
directions: Layer and cover with soft bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana brunch cake
directions: Combine pancake mix, 3/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add bananas, milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Spread into pan; combine 1/4 cup brown sugar and margarine and sprinkle evenly over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Combine blueberries, 1/3 cup sugar, lemon rind and water. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: pistachio-coconut surprise
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix.
Add coconut and pineapple and stir until blended.
Spoon into loaf pan and freeze until firm (at least 3 hours).
Remove from freezer to thaw before serving.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in pineapple until blended.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat. Gradually stir 1 cup hot filling into egg yolks; return all to pan, stirring constantly.
Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice.
Keep warm.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer in above order.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: easy corn fritters
directions: Mix all together and drop by tablespoons in deep hot oil.
By deep frying, they will not absorb much oil. Drain on paper towel.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients well until soup mix is dissolved. Place chicken in buttered baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken. Bake at 350° until done.

title: german casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cook potatoes and carrots; drain. Mix catsup, meat, soups and vegetables together. Place in large casserole dish. Top with cheese and onion rings. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cherry jello delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pie filling, pineapple and juice, lemon juice and pecans.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion and cheese with eggplant. Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover with cracker crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: quick cheese snack
directions: Grease 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle chilies in bottom of pan.
Next sprinkle on layer of grated cheese.
Mix eggs, Bisquick and milk.
Pour over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until firm.
Cut in 1 inch squares.
Serve with toothpicks. This freezes very well.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Cook the raspberries, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cool. Fold in berries.
Fill pie shell and cover with Cool Whip.

title: fritos salad
directions: Prepare ahead.
Brown ground beef; drain well.
Chill before making salad.
Assemble remainder of ingredients.
Combine all, except dressing, with chilled beef.
Add dressing when ready to serve.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Rub pork chops with a mixture of flour, salt, paprika and mustard.
Fry in hot fat until brown.
Slice onion over chops; add remaining ingredients.
Cook chops slowly or bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: chicken and fruit medley
directions: In a plastic bag, combine flour, ginger and salt.
Add chicken and shake until well coated; reserve flour mixture.
In a large skillet, melt butter and brown chicken on both sides.
Remove to baking dish.
Add leftover flour mixture to remaining drippings in pan; stir over low heat until smooth.
Slowly add liquid from pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges, then lemon juice, stirring constantly.
Simmer until thickened.
Meanwhile, spread pineapple chunks, oranges and apple over chicken, then add sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon surprise
directions: Drain mandarin oranges.
Do not drain fruit cocktail or pineapple.
Place all in bowl.
Slice bananas into bowl.
Add lemon juice and powdered instant pudding.
Mix all together.
Take a few minutes to thicken.
(May be used as a salad or dessert.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook together sugar, peanut butter and milk. When a soft ball is formed when dropping in cold water, remove from fire and add vanilla. Cool and beat until creamy. Press in 8 x 10 pan (buttered or sprayed).
When beginning to harden, cut in squares.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagne noodles, drain and place on sheets of wax paper. Cook meat, drain well and add spaghetti sauce; set aside.
Mix Ricotta cheese with 1 1/2 teaspoon of salt, 1 egg and 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon cheese mixture evenly on each noodle and roll up.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Put 1 cup of sauce mixture on bottom of pan and top with Lasagne Roll-Ups. Top with Mozzarella cheese, then with sauce mixture.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove foil and bake for another 10 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix salt and sugar.
Add melted shortening, eggs and yeast which has been dissolved in warm water.
Mix and add flour.
Put into refrigerator overnight. Roll out 1 1/2 to 2 hours before baking.

title: shredded sweet potatoes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Add flour and mix well.
Add pineapple, then milk and potatoes.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: vanilla custard sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine

sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in milk until smooth. Stir in corn syrup and egg yolk. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium-low heat and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Boil together for a few minutes the raisins and water.
Mix together sugar, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Add baking soda, baking powder, flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and nuts.
Gradually add water and raisins.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well; shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts or bacon bits.
Chill and serve.

title: diabetic pumpkin custard
directions: Beat eggs; combine with sweetener.
Add milk; mix well.
Stir in spices and pumpkin; blend.
Pour into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test by inserting knife near the edge.
When it comes out clean, the custard is finished. Cut into 6 equal portions when chilled.
This custard will keep the pie wedge shape without a crust.

title: microwave bean-burger bake
directions: Crumble ground beef into casserole; stir in onion.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes (until no longer pink).
Drain.
Stir in bacon and other ingredients.
(Bacon can be microwaved on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp, then drain.)
Microwave casserole dish, with all ingredients mixed in, on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking.
Yields about 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate-amaretto pudding
directions: Place egg in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and next 3 ingredients in a small saucepan; stir well. Gradually add milk, stirring with a whisk until smooth.
Place over medium-low heat and cook 15 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add half of hot milk mixture to egg, stirring constantly.
Return egg mixture to pan.
Place over medium-low heat and cook 2 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in Amaretto and vanilla.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Cover surface of pudding with plastic wrap and chill thoroughly.
Uncover and sprinkle evenly with almonds.
Makes 2 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Stir in mayonnaise and mustard.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, egg whites, onion, broccoli, cottage cheese, pepper, croutons and milk with a wooden spoon.
Pour into a lightly sprayed (with vegetable spray) casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.
Contains 258 calories, 4.2 gm fat, 6.3 mg cholesterol and 620 mg sodium per serving.

title: dill pickles
directions: Let salt, water and vinegar come to a boil.
Keep warm.
Fill jars with cucumbers.
Add lump of alum (size of a pea), 2 slices of onion, 2 cloves of garlic and 2 teaspoons of dill seed.
Fill jars with hot liquid and seal jars.
Makes 6 to 7 jars.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and onion together; drain.
In a skillet, mix oleo, flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
When thick, add milk and cheese.
Alternate cabbage and sauce in casserole.
End with bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Place beef in Dutch oven.
Combine all remaining ingredients. Pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 5 hours.
Shred beef with fork.
Serve on buns.
Makes 24 servings.

title: banana blueberries delight pie
directions: Blend together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Slice banana on bottom of cooked pie shell.
Cover with cream cheese filling.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: spicy texas chili
directions: Cover, cook over medium heat until releases juices and turns gray, about 30 minutes.
Uncover, cook juice away.
Then turn meat in rendered fat until well browned on all sides, 30 minutes more. Lift out meat and set aside.

title: english trifle
directions: Cut pound cake into 1-inch squares and arrange closely together in a 1 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Pour prepared gelatin over cake and refrigerate until set.
Chop 1/2 can peaches into bite-size pieces and sprinkle over cake.

title: chocolate cake
directions: This recipe can be halved if desired.

title: debra's chicken rice dinner
directions: Mix 1 cup water and 3 cans soup into rice and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Dip chicken breast pieces in melted margarine and place on top of rice and soup mixture. Crush the envelope of onion soup and sprinkle over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is well done.

title: cucumber cinnamon apple rings
directions: Peel cucumbers. Cut out centers with doughnut cutter hole to make rings. (Use centers, too, because they are too good to waste.)

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease shallow 2-quart baking dish. Spread chicken and vegetables evenly in prepared dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in small mixing bowl; pour evenly over chicken mixture.

title: spring temptation pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl for about two minutes.
Stir in sherbet; mix until melted.
Refrigerate 25 minutes or until gelatin mixture is slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping, marshmallows and pineapple.
Pour into crusts. Freeze until firm.
Makes two pies.
